title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt. Melt margarine in pot over low heat. Add oil, water and cocoa and let come to a boil. Stir in flour mixture after turning pot off heat.
Stir soda in buttermilk and add eggs and vanilla. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 12 x 18-inch or 2 small oblong pans.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in peeling until tender; peel and slice, place in greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan, and bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thick.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix; place in heavy pot.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans and soak overnight.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Thoroughly beat egg whites and add sugar while beating. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop on brown paper.
Place in 350° preheated oven, then turn oven off. Forget them. Leave in oven overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together well.
Roll into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Press out with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Great for kids!

title: ice cream cake dessert
directions: Mix the saltine cracker crumbs, graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: stromboli
directions: Let dough rise, punch down, knead lightly and roll out on a greased cookie sheet.
Layer the meat and cheese alternately across the dough.
Sprinkle with oregano, mushrooms, chopped peppers, onions or anything else you like.
Roll up sides of dough over meat and cheese as you would a jelly roll.
Fold ends in and turn over.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Tomato sauce or spaghetti sauce can be added.

title: asparagus plate
directions: Boil asparagus in salted water for 10 minutes.
Mix soup, milk, lemon juice, egg, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly

title: baby food cake
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients well.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup Pet milk; set aside.
Melt butter with 1/3 cup Pet milk and add to cake mix.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans if desired.
Put 1/2 cake mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Press in firmly.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Take from oven and put on chocolate chips.
Pour caramel mixture over top and put remaining cake mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: spicy meatball appetizers
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake, uncovered, in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and put in crock-pot.
Cover with chili sauce and grape jelly and cook on low for 2 hours.

title: creamed peas
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add cornstarch.
Cook and stir constantly.
Add milk and peas.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.

title: potato scallop
directions: Saute onion in butter 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and seasoning. Cook over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened. Add cheese.
Mix well.
Layer 1/2 of potatoes in greased casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of cheese sauce.
Repeat potato and cheese sauce.
Bake 1 hour, covered, then uncover and bake an additional 15 to 30 minutes until golden brown on 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cook unpeeled cucumbers in water overnight.
Slice cucumbers and onions and place in pan and sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour and rinse.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric powder.
Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Pack pickles in hot jars.
Close.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes. Start to count processing as soon as water returns to boiling.

title: aunt margaret's and mary's crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Place Crisco and salt in boiling water.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat eggs.
Mix in sugar.
Add water mixture to eggs.
Add yeast.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour gradually.
Place in bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough in 2 rounds 1/2-inch thick, 3 hours or more before serving.
Spread with butter.
Cut in pie shaped wedges.
Roll starting at large end. Let rise 3 hours on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Yields 24 to 36 rolls.

title: hasty hash brown frittata
directions: In a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate, put potatoes, mushrooms, pepper and onion.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on full power until pepper is crisp-tender (4 to 5 minutes).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine four, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, egg yolks, Cool Whip and butter; set aside.
Then tear cake in bite size pieces.
Put layer of cake, then Cool Whip mixture, then Butterfingers.
Repeat until all is gone.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake.
Mix in punch bowl 2 cups milk and pudding. Add condensed milk; fold in 12 ounces Cool Whip.
Layer in punch bowl pudding mixture, cake (broken up) and fruits (bananas, cherries, coconut, pineapple and chopped pecans).
Top with 16 ounces Cool Whip.

title: chicken ball
directions: In large bowl, mix first six ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Shape mixture into ball, and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Note:
Ball may also be rolled in crumbled bacon, chives or a combination of bacon, chives and nuts.

title: cold rice with shrimp
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and cool.
Chop scallions, chives and onion fine.
Add to the cold cooked rice. Add the shrimp and mayonnaise.
Season to taste with the ginger, salt and lemon juice and refrigerate until serving time.
Heap on lettuce and garnish with sesame seed.

title: tortoni
directions: Mix egg white and salt with rotary beater until stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to this.
Whip cream and 4 tablespoons sugar; add flavors.
Mix cream and egg whites together.
Spoon into cupcake cups and freeze until firm.
Enjoy!

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until served.
Makes 6 servings (45 calories/1/2 cup serving). Trace of protein, Carbohydrates 9, Fat 1, Trace of Cholesterol, Sodium 145.

title: red cake
directions: In a bowl, cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs.
Cream. In a small bowl, mix food coloring and 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Add to creamed mixture. Add the following ingredients alternately to creamed mixture:
buttermilk or sour milk, salt and flour.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together thoroughly sugar and shortening. Stir in buttermilk, mashed bananas and flour, then stir in soda. Then fold in nuts. Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream peanut butter, shortening and vanilla.
Beat in sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat
butter
and
cream cheese
together.
Add
sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a
time,
beating
after each. Add vanilla. Sift flour once;
measure
and
sift
again with salt. Blend dry ingredients into
creamed mixture.
Beat 3 minutes. Spoon into a 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat chicken broth in a large pot. Add salt and pepper.
Beat eggs in a small bowl. When broth is hot, pour eggs very slowly into broth. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Combine cooked rice, milk, sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on Medium (50% power) for 13 to 15 minutes, stirring evenly every 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter.
Add vanilla and sugar gradually; cream well.
Sift flour and salt together; add to creamed mixture, working in well with hands.
Blend in nuts.
Form into small balls.
Bake ion a slow oven on ungreased cookie sheet 15 minutes (approximately).
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: creole steak
directions: Lightly flour meat and brown in hot oil; set aside.
Saut onion and pepper.
Combine all ingredients except parsley, simmer 45-50 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice tossed with parsley. Serves 8.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Add sugar and boiling water.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve with milk or ice cream.
Best warm.

title: english mustard vinaigrette
directions: Blend dry ingredients; add oil slowly, stirring briskly.
Add vinegar and mix.
Use as a dressing over romaine or green leaf lettuce.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese. Gradually add powdered sugar and milk, then vanilla and Cool Whip. Spread in pie shells. Chill.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt in a sifter and sift into shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine
all ingredients in crock-pot.	Cook slow for 8 to 10 hours, stirring occasionally.
This is the best!

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet with onion; then drain and place in a baking dish.
Add in beans, ketchup, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Stir and bake for about 1/2 hour in oven at 350°.

title: sweet taters
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pare and cut in thick slices.
Boil in enough water to cover until not quite tender.
Drain and arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Melt butter and brown sugar together.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 400° until potatoes are brown and syrup is thickened, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove cover last half of baking.
Cover with mini marshmallows last 5 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine, then mix with all ingredients.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on edges.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Add sugar, stirring, until sugar is moistened with the chocolate mixture.
Add evaporated milk and continue cooking and stirring until smooth. Add vanilla.
Makes about 1 quart.
Can be stored in refrigerator and reheated whenever desired.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, then mix all other ingredients in large bowl. Add yeast, mix well. Store covered in refrigerator with cloth. Use as desired.

title: fat-free muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese onto bottom of casserole dish; pour chili on top and spread over cream cheese.
Pour salsa over chili, then add taco cheese.
Bake at 350° or microwave until taco cheese is melted.
Serve with corn chips or plain Tostitos.

title: lynne's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese, Marshmallow Fluff and flour until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, just until mixed.
Pour into crust and bake 45 minutes (until edges start to brown).
Turn off heat, let cool for one hour with door cracked open.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Top with fruit, berries, whipped cream, etc.

title: velvet salad dressing
directions: Beat egg well.
Add dry ingredients, vinegar and water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and beat in 3 tablespoons oleo. Dressing for potato salad.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and vanilla.
Add Corn Flakes and desired amount of green food coloring.
Stir until well mixed. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper or cookie sheet, then garnish with red hots.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda and spices.
Lightly beat together the orange rind, orange juice, egg and oil.
Stir the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients.
Coarsely chop the cranberries and add to the batter along with the chopped nuts.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Partially thaw strawberries.
Mix whipped topping and strawberries.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Grind wafers and put most of them in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream 1/2 cup butter.
Add a cup of powdered sugar and cream well.
Add yolk of eggs.
Fold in 2 well-beaten egg whites.
Drop mixture by small spoonfuls over ground wafers and spread carefully over crumbs.
Put in refrigerator until it hardens a little.
Over this, spread 2 to 3 cups mashed apricots (sweetened).
Let the apricots get to room temperature before putting on butter and egg mixture.
Whip the whipping cream and spread over the apricots. (Add the vanilla and 1 teaspoon sugar to the whipped cream.) Garnish with a little of the ground wafers.
Place in the refrigerator.
Can make the night before; will keep several days.

title: southwestern chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken breast along with garlic, onion and water.
Add the broth of cooked chicken plus 2 cans of Swanson broth to well washed beans.
Cook until tender.
(If more liquid is needed, add water.)
Add tomatoes, chili mix and "shredded chicken".
Simmer for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Scald milk and cracker crumbs.
Mix together sugar, coconut and eggs.
Add to milk mixture and bring to a boil.
Add vanilla. Yummy good, either hot or real cold.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together well.
Drop by level tablespoons into hot oil. Fry until completely cooked, about 5 minutes; drain.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Mix meat, rice, garlic, pepper, onion and egg.
Place 1/2 of cabbage on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put meat mixture on top of cabbage.
Add rest of cabbage.
Mix tomato soup, juice and water.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana luncheon loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add bananas and bake 60 to 70 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: seasoned chicken and new potatoes(preacher randy's favorite)
directions: Lay chicken in glass 9 x 13 pan.

Cover with sliced new potatoes, sliced bell peppers and sliced onions. Sprinkle with crushed garlic, parsley flakes, garlic salt, thyme and salt and pepper. Place 2 bay leaves on top and drizzle olive oil all over top. Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour. Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar
well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add dry
ingredients, small amount each time; beat well. Add other ingredients;
mix
well.
Cook in 3 layers at 325°.

title: cinnamon apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Grease a 12-portion standard size muffin pan. Sift together the flour, cinnamon, and brown sugar. In another bowl, combine the eggs, buttermilk, and oil. Beat until blended. Combine the two mixtures, stirring only until mixed. Do not beat with an electric mixer.

Stir in the apples. Spoon into prepared muffin tin, filling each section about 1/2 full. If you have batter leftover, spoon it evenly into the cups. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of a muffin.
Turn out of pan immediately. Good served warm with butter!

title: southern biscuits
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add self rising flour and baking soda.
Add Crisco and mix with fork until size of small marbles. Add milk all at once.
Blend quickly with wooden spoon by working gently and quickly (at this point dough will be light and flaky). Use 1/4 cup of flour to sprinkle over dough at this point.
(This will keep the dough from sticking to fingers as turning dough.) Turn and fold dough into a smooth ball.
Turn and knead 4 to 5 times.
Using forefinger and thumb squeeze off a portion of dough about the size of large eggs.
Repeat.
Place in a greased, medium size iron skillet, each biscuit touching.
After pan is full, with palm of hand, press each biscuit firmly.
Spread 2 Tbsp. melted Crisco over top of biscuits.
Preheat oven to 475° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix well shortening and sugar, then add egg yolks; beat well. Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Beat the egg whites at room temperature until nice and stiff, then fold into batter.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cleaned, washed and dried blueberries over the batter, then pour rest of batter over berries.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain and cut dills into 1/2-inch chunks.
Place pickles into pint jars.
Add garlic.
Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Add spices.
Pour over pickles and spoon spices into each jar; put lids on jars and shake every day for few days. Should be kept refrigerated, but will keep if sealed on shelf.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, cherry filling and marshmallows.
Stir well.
This sets immediately so can be served in minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: In a greased pan, put ingredients in order as listed.
First rhubarb, 2nd Jell-O and 3rd dry cake mix.
Pour melted oleo and water over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: After you have cooked your rice and drained and thawed your box of broccoli, mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish. Cook about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cheese coconut cake
directions: Batter:
Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add 2 egg yolks, beating well after each (other 2 yolks are used in the filling). Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well.
Add vanilla and soda water.
Beat egg whites; fold in last.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: swedish nut pineapple cake
directions: Mix the six ingredients together well and bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: perchy pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Rinse the fish; pat dry on a paper towel and place in a baking pan.
Season both sides of fish with oil, margarine, spike, salt and pepper and juice from squeezed lemon.
Top with paprika.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Boil pasta 10 minutes in uncovered pot, stirring occasionally.
Drain.

title: apple brownies
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs; sift dry ingredients and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 2 cups diced apples.
Mix together and spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: seasoning mixture for crabs
directions: In a large container, mix all ingredients.
Mix well and put in airtight container to store for later use.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 baking dish. Stir and press in crumbs. Mix milk, sour cream and lemon juice, then spread over crumb mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cinnamon and pecans.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in pans, then make the sauce.
Put half and half into a heavy pot and add about half the oleo and cayenne.
Dissolve in 1/2 cup water the chicken base and add to the milk mixture.
Grate the cheese and put into sauce.
Add about 3 or 4 tablespoons cornstarch and stir until the consistency of custard.
Pour the sauce over the potatoes and melt the remaining oleo and pour over the top.
Place in oven and start at 300° for a few minutes, then raise to 350° and bake until brown.
This will serve 50 people.
This recipe was given to the club in 1968 by Mrs. Winthrop Rockefeller's cook, Ben Mitchell.
When I use it, I break it down to one fourth of all ingredients.
It works great.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal; toss lightly with fork. Add next 5 ingredients; beat with rotary or electric mixer until smooth and blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cut while warm.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onions and spices.
Add ketchup, soups and mustard.
Mix well and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve on hamburger rolls, 15 to 20 sandwiches.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir flour, soda and salt together.
In a mixer bowl, beat margarine, applesauce and oil for 30 seconds.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and maple extract.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture and beat until well combined.
Stir in chocolate morsels* and nuts.

title: pineapple supreme congealed salad
directions: Dissolve lime and lemon gelatin in hot water.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into rectangular dish (13 x 6 x 2-inch) and chill.
When firm, cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: curry chicken
directions: Clean the chicken.
Cut the chicken in quarters.
In a skillet melt the butter and vegetable oil.
Sprinkle garlic powder into butter and vegetable oil.
Season the chicken with the curry powder, pepper and salt.
Place chicken into skillet.
Brown all chicken pieces on both sides for about 10 minutes.
When chicken is brown, remove from pan.
Add onions and green pepper in skillet. Add chicken and cut quartered potatoes.
Sprinkle with more curry; let simmer covered.
Add 1 cup of water at 1/2 hour.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 5.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except flour) and beat until creamy.
Add flour and mix well.
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Dampen a glass and dip in sugar, then press each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a medium-sized saucepan over medium heat, combine rice, 1 1/2 cups milk, sugar and sweetener.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thick and slightly creamy.
Beat remaining milk and egg; stir into rice mixture.
Stir in raisins. Continue cooking slowly for 2 minutes.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Mixture will thicken as it stands.
Pour into serving bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings with 120 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: mexicali crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix first 4 ingredients in roasting pan. On stove mix remaining ingredients.
When mixture boils, pour over dry ingredients and make sure it's coated well.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour on wax paper to cool.
Works great for goody baskets, especially at Christmas.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, in oil, brown roast on all sides; spoon off fat.
Add vegetables.
Stir in mushroom and onion soups and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low, cover.
Cook 45 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash the avocados.
Remove seeds and chop chilies and tomatoes.
Chop cilantro and combine all ingredients.
Put in a serving dish with the avocado seed in center.
This prevents discoloration.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: old south pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Serves 8.

title: gooey pecan bars
directions: Mix
together and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: potato soup surprise
directions: Use a heavy kettle, combine the 1st 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until cabbage is cooked.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough mix onto a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar granules and dissolve.
Spread cream cheese mixture over the cookie dough once it has cooled.
Top with fruit.

title: fabulous french toast(servings:  4)
directions: Beat the eggs and cream together.
Add the Triple Sec, granulated sugar, orange zest and cinnamon; whisk until well blended.
Pour into a shallow bowl or pie plate.
Dip each croissant half in the egg mixture, turning once.
Melt a few tablespoons of the butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Add as many croissants as will fit and fry until golden on both sides. Repeat with the remaining croissants, adding butter to the skillet as needed.
Sift confectioners sugar over the croissants.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
6 portions.

title: lavon's baked pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, flour and milk.
Pour into the casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top will be slightly brown, looks like fallen souffl.
Cut and serve warm with any topping: syrup, fruit (strawberries, peaches, berries).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili relleno
directions: Spread chili peppers in an 8-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam; layer cheeses evenly over.
Beat eggs with evaporated milk, flour and salt; pour over cheese and bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Then pour 1 (4 ounce) can tomato sauce over top and bake 7 minutes more or until center is set.
So delicious, always a winner.

title: old kentucky corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and sugar. Add milk slowly, stirring constantly over low heat until mixture thickens and boils.

Stir in corn and fold in well beaten eggs. Pour into greased 1-quart casserole and set in pan of hot water. Bake 15 minutes at 375°; lower temperature to 350° and continue baking about 30 minutes until set.
Serves 6.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak across the grain into strips.
Brown meat in hot oil in a large skillet.
Add the peppers, celery, onion, garlic, bouillon, salt and pepper; cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, water and cornstarch; stir well.
Add to meat mixture then cook stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: fish patties
directions: Cut fish into 1/4 to 1/2-inch cubes.
Beat eggs with a fork and add milk and Bisquick until well blended.
Mix in rest of ingredients; put in fish last.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Drop by large spoonfuls in hot oiled skillet.
Brown over medium heat until golden brown.
Turn once.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Cool 1 minute and serve.

title: marinated beans
directions: Drain beans; slice and add the onions and olives.
Add tomatoes.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar; pour over the vegetable mixture; add dressing to cover.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours or longer.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: Put peaches in bottom of pie pan.
Cover peaches with the slices of bread.
Mix sugar, egg, milk, flour and butter and pour over bread slices.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until bread is a light brown.

title: clem's easter cheese
directions: You will also need cheesecloth.

title: savannah anderson's strawberries
directions: Put berries and vinegar in covered pan and boil 1 minute.
Add sugar and boil 20 minutes.
Set off and cool overnight.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Stir in pineapple including juice. Fold in bread.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated fruit
directions: Combine fruits and sprinkle the vanilla pudding mix and Tang over fruit and mix.
Make sure apples and bananas are well coated. Refrigerate covered overnight.
Serve.
(Optional:
If strawberries are desired, add fresh small whole strawberries 15 minutes only before serving!)
Great for breakfast, salad or dessert!

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef; drain, then mix other ingredients with beef.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: taters
directions: Prepare potatoes per instructions; add other ingredients and mix.
Kids love this.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 cup onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir and top with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes more and serve.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Use a large Pyrex dish.
Melt all of the butter.
Add 1 pack of crushed crackers.
In a large bowl, mix crackers, mushroom soup, boiled chicken, sour cream and poppy seed.
Pour onto crackers and butter, then crumble other pack of crackers and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Make balls. Place in freezer for a while to set.
Melt wax and chocolate together.
Then dip in balls one at a time.
Place on wax paper to set.
Then place in freezer.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into a 13 x 9 casserole dish. Add grated cheese. Mix together flour and sugar. Stir flour and sugar in the pineapple and cheese. Crush 30 Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Melt margarine and pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meatball casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt, oregano and pepper over meat.
Add bread crumbs and evaporated milk; mix well.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti in boiling salted water; drain and rinse.
Stir spaghetti together with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Remove 2 tablespoons of drippings from meat and add to spaghetti.
Drain remaining fat from meat.
Spread spaghetti mixture evenly over meat to form layer; pour spaghetti sauce evenly over top. Continue baking 15 minutes.
Arrange cheese slices on top and sprinkle with olives; continue baking additional 5 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute ground beef on medium heat until done.
Drain all grease from meat.
Add taco seasoning.
Next clean lettuce and tomatoes. Drain juice from olives.
Cut up lettuce and tomatoes and mix together.
Add olives.
Crush Doritos.
Peel and slice avocado for garnish.
When ready to serve, mix all ingredients together.
Use Italian dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust with your choice of decorative edge, then preheat oven to 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: almond chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, covered with foil, with a small amount of water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce to 300°. Cook until tender (about 4 to 5 hours).
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.
Combine all ingredients, then put chicken pieces into this batter.
Mix well.
Pinch out nugget size amounts and drop into clean hot oil in a large Dutch oven.
Cook until golden, lift out of oil with a slotted spoon and place on paper towels to drain.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Place seasonings, cheese, parsley and crumbs in plastic bag. Coat chicken by shaking in bag.
Oil shallow roasting pan.
Pour in water and arrange chicken pieces.
Sprinkle chicken with oil and melted margarine and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Pour wine over chicken and cook for additional 15 minutes.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, stir sugar and syrup until well mixed.
Add pecans and salt, mixing well.
Microwave on high for 6 to 9 minutes until light brown.
Be careful removing this from the microwave as it is extremely hot.
Add butter and vanilla and stir well.
Microwave on high for 1 to 2 minutes more.
Pecans will be light brown and syrup will be hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly buttered cookie sheet and spread out.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat egg yolks and combine with sugar, butter, flour, lemon juice and milk. Fold in egg whites. Pour into crust and bake at 375° until firm.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour or shake in sack.
Wrap 2 or 3 slices bacon around each chicken breast.
Layer baking dish with dried beef and place chicken on beef.
Combine sour cream and soup and spread over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours, covered and 1/2 hour, uncovered at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot turkey sandwiches
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot margarine, cook carrots, onion, celery and thyme until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in gravy.
Heat to boiling.
Add turkey.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Divide turkey and gravy mixture evenly among bread slices.
If desired, serve with apples and grapes. Garnish with fresh thyme.

title: oven barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ready to use.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry diced salt pork until golden.
Remove scraps (3 tablespoons of fat).
Cook 2 diced onions in fat until yellow.
Add 4 cups potato pieces.
Add water.
Add fish fillet (haddock) on top.
Add pepper and salt.
Cook to a boil, then even heat until fish flakes in big chunks.
Pour in 2 to 3 cups milk plus 1 large (13 ounce) can evaporated milk.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Add to cake mix, eggs, shortening and water.
This batter can be formed into a roll and chilled, then sliced for refrigerator cookies, dropped by spoonfuls for drop cookies or rolled into balls and flattened for decorated cookies.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
By adding nuts, fruit or chips or substituting ingredients, this recipe will make an endless variety of cookies.

title: easy breakfast strata
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage and drain. In large bowl, beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch deep baking dish. Cover; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: poor boy cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until 1 cup of liquid is left.
Then add the shortening, sugar, cinnamon, ground cloves, ground allspice, soda, salt, flour and chopped nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a large flat cake pan.
Ice while warm with powdered sugar icing.

title: rich mushroom soup
directions: Place mushrooms, onion, salt and pepper in butter in a large saucepan. Saute 5 minutes. Stir in flour. Add chicken broth and soy sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add cream and reheat to piping hot. Serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften bouillon cubes in hot water. Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Use as dip for raw vegetables.

title: skillet lemon chicken
directions: About 30 minutes before serving:
From lemon, grate 1/2 teaspoon peel; squeeze 1 tablespoon juice.
On a sheet of waxed paper, mix grated lemon peel, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon flour.
Use to coat chicken breast halves.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
In large pan, pour juice, salt, food coloring, cherries and pineapple; bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add to fruit little at a time, cooking until thick.
Add vanilla and cool.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops at 300°
in electric frying pan . Take chops out.
Simmer 6 beef bouillon cubes and 3 cups boiling water.
Stir and dissolve.
Add rice, celery, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper. Mix.
Place chops on top.
Can also be topped with onions, peppers or tomatoes.
Cook; simmer 45 to 50 minutes.
Add water if necessary.

title: coconut pecan filling and frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, oleo and vanilla in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until cool and of spreading consistency.
Great on oatmeal or German chocolate cake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix together salt, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and flour, then add to first mixture.
Then add carrots and walnuts; mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: company lamb chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat; season.
Place in baking pan.
Top each with green pepper ring, onion slice and lemon slice.
Pour tomato juice over chops.
Cover, bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Slice onion in rings, saute in butter, set aside.
Add together Jiffy mix, egg, 1/3 cup milk, creamed corn and Tabasco.
Place this in greased baking dish (larger than 8-inches square, although I've used 8-inch and was happy.)
Add to sauteed onion, the sour cream, salt, dill weed, 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Spread over batter and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese.
In a preheated oven, bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one dish stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain off grease.
Add rice and onion soup mix.
Line bottom of casserole dish with chopped up cabbage. Cover cabbage with meat mixture; cover with more cabbage.
Pour tomato sauce on top; add enough water to cover top layer.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until liquid has absorbed.

title: oven rice
directions: Saut rice in butter until chalky. Put in 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour broth, mushrooms and onions into pan. Add rosemary. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. You can make this a main dish by putting chicken breasts on the bottom and only using 1 can of broth. Follow directions given.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Fill a large bowl with lettuce.
Add other vegetables in layers.
Spread mayonnaise and sprinkle sugar on top.
Cover with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pan with oil or butter.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and beer.
Mix with a wooden spoon until well blended and sticky, about 1 minute.
Then pour mix into prepared loaf pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Take out and pour melted butter over bread.
Put back in oven for 30 more minutes or until done.
Take out and cool in pan.
Remove from pan and slice. Serve with butter.

title: easy s.o.s.
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until bubbles form on edge of pan. Spoon over toast.
Makes 6 to 8 pieces.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Add nuts and salt.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla with baking soda and stir in quickly.
Immediately pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: german oven pancakes
directions: Melt butter in pie plate or 8-inch iron skillet in oven.
Beat eggs, milk, flour and salt together.
Pour into pie plate or skillet when butter has melted.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. When done, pour off excess butter and fill with fresh fruit or sausage and scrambled eggs.
Makes 1 pancake.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix in order as given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes a lot of cookies.

title: katie's favorite broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion, carrot and broccoli.
Add milk, bouillon, sugar and nutmeg.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Do not overcook.

title: shrimp & broccoli packets
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees or grill to medium-high.
Spray foil with nonstick spray.
Center one-half of shrimp on each sheet of Reynolds Wrap Aluminum Foil.
Arrange rice around shrimp; sprinkle with remaining garlic and top with butter.
Place ice cubes on top.
Bring up foil sides.
Double fold top and one end. Through open end, pour in water.
Double fold remaining end to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.
Repeat to make two packets.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low setting for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve on sliced French rolls with juices on the side for dipping.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello and marshmallows in the hot water.
Cool to thicken.
Drain the pineapple and whip the juice and cream cheese together.
Add the pineapple and nuts.
Add to thickened jello and marshmallows.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 500°. Place margarine in a medium sized iron frying pan and melt. Mix meal and milk together and pour melted margarine into it, stirring well. Pour in pan and bake for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. In another bowl, combine buttermilk and egg.
Add corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Do not overmix.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cool, peel and chop potatoes.
Put in casserole.
Add crumbled bacon, onion, celery, eggs, salt and pepper.

title: dixie's apple dumplings
directions: Place brisket on large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Sprinkle with liquid smoke and salts.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight or at least 5 hours.
When ready to bake, sprinkle with lemon pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Reseal in foil.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Uncover and pour barbecue sauce over meat. Cook with foil open for another 1/2 hour.
Remove to platter and let cool before slicing.
Remove fat and discard from remaining juice in dish.
Place in saucepan; add flour, water and additional barbecue sauce (to taste and to thicken).
Serve sauce with sliced meat.
I serve sliced brisket with sauce, mayonnaise and rolls (Kroger Country Oven) to be eaten as a sandwich.
Serve with large green salad, baked beans and dessert.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 15 x 10 1/4 x 3/4-inch cookie sheet.
Cool. Prepare pudding according to box directions.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry ham with soy sauce. Add carrots. Stir-fry to heat through. Add onions, rice and peas.
Mix and heat over medium heat.
Make a well in the center so bottom of pan is exposed. Add eggs and cook, stirring constantly, until soft scrambled, then mix into rice mixture.

title: italian pot roast and noodles
directions: Sprinkle roast with meat tenderizer 30 minutes before cooking. Saute onions in butter.
Brown roast on both sides.
Add water, salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Cook roast about 2 hours.
Add mushrooms, olives and tomato sauce; cook 1 hour longer.
Serve with noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, molasses, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch closely; they burn easily.

title: canned apples
directions: At least 8 to 12 hours before canning, peel and quarter apples.
(You want 2 gallons
of peeled and quartered apples.) Wash
and
spread
apples
in
shallow
container.
Not
tin. Sprinkle 5 cups sugar over all.
Apples
form their own syrup. After 8 to 12 hours, put into
quart
jars.
Finish filling jars with water.
To seal, cook in
water
bath
20 minutes or until apples begin to burst.
If
cooked
too
long, they collapse; too little and they are hard.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking pan or dish and cover with Swiss cheese. Spread stuffing mix over chicken and cover with soup and margarine. Bake at 350° until done and tender.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and stir well.
This can be made the day before serving. Refrigerate.

title: aunt ella's chicken paprika
directions: Cut each breast in half so that there are 4 pieces.
Saute cutlets in oil until almost golden brown and add onion to meat. Saute with chicken until golden in color (use medium Dutch oven). Add chicken broth, tomato juice and spices and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Remove chicken to platter and keep warm.
Thicken juices in pot with cornstarch and water mixture.
When thickened, add sour cream and blend until smooth.
(If desired, sauteed mushrooms add a lot to this dish.)
Pour sour cream mixture over chicken and serve with hot noodles.
Serves 4.
tags: amount of cornstarch mixed with equal amount of water

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients.
Brown ground meat and drain on paper towel.
Chop onion, grate cheese and chop jalapeno pepper.

title: chili-mac skillet
directions: In large skillet brown meat, drain fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, uncooked pasta, green chiles, chili powder, garlic salt and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Cover, simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
Top with cheese, cover until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, butter, egg and water.
Add dry ingredients. Bake at 350° in a floured and greased loaf pan for 45 minutes or until done.

title: daniel's chicken divan
directions: Arrange chicken in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and mushrooms in a large bowl and set aside.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and cream.
Add orange peel.
Sift dry ingredients except soda.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add milk and most of flour alternately.
Mix remainder of flour with dates and pecans.
Add to batter.
Bake in slow oven at 250° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: cracker drops
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir to dissolve.
Add pecans, vanilla and crackers.
Beat until it starts to harden. Drop onto wax paper with teaspoon.
Makes 35.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a deep 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high heat.
Add the oil, then the elbow macaroni and cook until the macaroni is just tender, about 7 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Return to the cooking pot.

title: gazpacho
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes, cucumber, bell pepper and onion. Combine in a large bowl.
In an electric blender, blend tomato juice, cloves, olive oil and vinegar.
Add to chopped mixture. Serve with warm tortillas topped with melted cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese balls
directions: Roll into balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes. Cook until done in about 1/2 cup of water (about 20 minutes or more). Drain. Cream potatoes with mixer, adding sugar and butter. Separate an egg and use the beaten yolk of egg in cream mixture. Beat well. Add vanilla flavoring. Place in greased baking dish.

title: orange cake
directions: Combine cake and pudding mixes in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring into dry ingredients.
Add oil and water.
Mix until smooth.
Add orange peel and stir in.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° in a tube or Bundt pan.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Cook noodles until about half done, then drain.
Heat sauce and pepperoni together until hot.
Put noodles into dish, then add sauce and pepperoni.
Stir in cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° until bubbly (about 20 minutes).

title: cuddle dogs
directions: Grill jumbo franks.
Warm tortilla according to package directions.
Lay flour tortilla flat; sprinkle with bacon bits. Wrap one slice of cheese around frank.
Roll frank up in flour tortilla.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted.
Dip in honey mustard sauce or any of your favorite sauces.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chili sauce
directions: Boil all together until as thick as desired.

title: mushroom soup and meat balls
directions: Mix beef, onion and bell pepper.
Roll out in balls.
Fry until brown; drain fat.
In saucepan mix 1 can water and can of mushroom soup.
Cook until creamy.
Pour over meat balls and cook on low heat until brown.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Boil the onions until tender; drain. Heat 4 tablespoons of the butter in a skillet and saut the onions. Beat the eggs and milk together. Add the onions, half the cracker crumbs, the cheese and salt and pepper to taste. Bake in a buttered casserole at 375° for 35 minutes. Melt the remaining 3 tablespoons butter and stir it into the remaining cracker crumbs. Top the casserole with the buttered crumbs and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: dairy state fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter together.
Soften bark in double boiler or microwave.
Add cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add nuts and beat 7 to 10 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pan and cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers,
in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Add the crushed Ritz crackers. Melt oleo and drizzle over crackers.
Cook 45 minutes at 425°.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all together and place in tightly covered jar.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix the melted margarine and the corn.
Add the eggs and sour cream and mix well.
Stir in corn muffin mix.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart ungreased deep dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, ginger, cinnamon and salt; dissolve soda in hot water.
Melt shortening and add sugar, molasses, egg and cold water; mix until creamy and add flour mixture, then add soda and water.
Add raisins and nuts.
Place by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Place oleo, Crisco, salt and flour in bowl.
Use mixer to cut until coarse (low speed).
Add water and work as little as possible.
Let set 2 hours.
Pinch off and roll (won't tear).
Can refrigerate leftovers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream
together
shortening,
sugars
and
eggs.
Add applesauce and water.
Sift flour once; measure and sift again with all other dry ingredients.
Beat into applesauce mixture, beating for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts and dates
or
raisins if desired. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Frost
with cream cheese frosting or caramel frosting when cool. Bake in
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: mud pudding
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
(I use a food processor for this.)
Mix butter and cream cheese.
Add pudding, milk, powdered sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Put Cool Whip lid in bottom of flower pot to keep crumbs from falling through the little hole.
Put a layer of cookies, then pudding, cookies, pudding, etc.
Save enough cookies to go on top so it will look like soil in your pot.
Add flowers (artificial) and worms (gummy worms).

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut all vegetables into chunks and roll in flour, salt, & pepper.
Fry in large skillet of hot oil until crispy brown.

title: orange-ginger spareribs
directions: Pour chilled peach nectar over a glass of ice, filling it about 2/3 full.
Add club soda and top with a pineapple, cherry and straw.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain.
Add all ingredients; then chill.

title: louisiana cherry bounce
directions: Combine all ingredients in gallon jug.
Shake to mix.
Let set, capped 6 weeks.
Stir occasionally.
Strain through cheesecloth into clean jug.
Discard cherries.

title: toni's chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix the chicken with salt, pepper and onion to taste.
Heat the soups and chilies in saucepan; mix enough of this mixture with chicken to make it stick together.

title: northwest apple pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 greased and floured jelly roll pans (10 x 15-inches).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add optional ingredients, if desired. Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: zippy clam dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil on medium heat.
Boil for one minute.
Add cornflakes and stir well.
Drop on a plate and cool.

title: peanut sauce(sauce from thailand)
directions: In a pan, heat the thick coconut milk over low heat and cook until it thickens and becomes oily around the edges.
Increase the heat.
Add the curry paste and cook for 3 to 5 minutes, being careful not to burn.
There will be a noticeable color and odor change as the mixture becomes properly cooked.
Add the thin coconut milk gradually and stir.
Season with fish sauce, sugar and Tamarind Water.
Add ground peanuts; stir and serve.

title: pineapple salad dressing
directions: Combine juice, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Mix eggs, water and flour to form a paste.
Add to juice mixture. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Keeps well.
Serve over any fruit mixture.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a very large bowl, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook in microwave uncovered on High for 5 minutes.
Add nuts and cook 13 to 15 minutes or until 300° reached on candy thermometer, checking last few minutes.

title: west indies salad
directions: In large bowl, carefully mix together crabmeat and onion.
In a small mixing bowl; mix together oil, vinegar, water and Italian dressing, mix well.
Pour mixture over crabmeat but do not stir. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours; but better if left for 12 hours.

title: deep fried zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini well and slice in thin pieces (1/8-inch) diagonally.
Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper or paper towels and get all the slices ready to fry at one time.
In 3 shallow bowls, place in one the flour to which the salt has been added and mixed well, in one the beaten eggs and in one the cracker meal. Place on cookie sheet.
When all is ready, heat at least 2 inches of cooking oil in a deep, heavy pot (I use a small one) or a deep fryer.
Drop a few zucchini slices at a time in hot oil and fry until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: caramel cheesecake
directions: Melt caramels with evaporated milk in microwave.
Begin with one minute on high, then stir and repeat for 30 seconds at a time until caramel is smooth.
Pour into crust. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour on top of caramel.
Bake at 350 degrees until mixture does not shake (approximately 30 minutes).

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Wash and drain strawberries, then slice and sprinkle with Equal or any other brand sweetener.
Prepare pudding according to directions except use water instead of milk.
When pudding comes to boiling according to box directions, add the sugar-free strawberry gelatin.
Mix well and cool.
Add sweetened strawberries.
Pour into graham cracker crust or other kind of crust.
Chill until set.
Serve with sugar-free Cool Whip.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, margarine and flour.
Take a small amount of this mixture and form into 1-inch balls.
Flatten slightly and place olive in center.
Roll back into ball.
Continue until either olives or mixture runs out.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
These can be stored in freezer before baking.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch and sugar.
Add water gradually and stir until boiling.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Store in glass jar and keep in a cool place.

title: chicken in beer
directions: Brown chicken parts (coated with flour or not) in oil; set aside.
In same skillet, add onions and brown slightly, shaking skillet.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Take from heat; cool until fat has risen to surface. Skim off fat.
Stir in the sour cream; reheat, but do not boil. Remove bay leaf.
Good with linguini or vermicelli noodles or small red potatoes.

title: chili and cheese rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, chiles, cream and one-half of the grated cheese. Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sandy's rice
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in casserole dish.
Dot margarine or butter on top.
Cover with lid or foil.
Cook in 375° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Place 1 cup sugar in heavy skillet and heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and browns (it should start to smoke).
Remove from heat and add boiling water.
Return to heat and stir until sugar is dissolved and syrup begins to thicken slightly (use wooden spoon for stirring).
Set aside to cool. Cream 1/2 cup shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add 2 eggs, beaten thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with 1 cup milk (room temperature).
Beat until blended after each addition.
Stir in burnt sugar syrup.
Pour batter into two 9-inch layer pans, which have been lined on the bottoms with wax paper and greased.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for about 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with Burnt Sugar Frosting.

title: burger loaf with sweet and sour glaze
directions: In small skillet, melt margarine and saute chopped onions and bread crumbs.
In large mixing bowl, combine onions and bread crumbs with vegetarian burger, cheese, eggs and spices.
Press into an oiled 9 x 9 x 2-inch square baking dish.

title: tangy party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine the first four ingredients. Stir in ginger ale.
Add scoops of sherbet.
Serve immediately. Yield: 8 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and blend together the 3 ingredients; roll into small balls (makes about 90).
Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: thelma's golden glow cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add 1 egg yolk at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, a small amount at a time; beat until smooth after each addition, adding vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Turn into 3 prepared layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread with chocolate or coconut icing.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil raisins, water and Crisco together until raisins are plump.
Add rest of ingredients to large bowl.
Stir to combine and then add boiled mixture to dry ingredients and stir well. Pour into greased tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
I bake this cake every Christmas.

title: pork chop in corn
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables and set aside.
Melt soup with cream cheese and add mayonnaise.
Stir in vegetable mixture and put in greased casserole.
Mix crackers and margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: alaskan salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry Jell-O together. Add cottage cheese, oranges and pineapple and chill well before serving.

title: lemon party meringue pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, 2/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup of the water in saucepan.
Blend in egg yolks and remaining water.
Cook and stir over medium heat, until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in lemon juice and butter.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell on lowest rack 4 to 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cook and crumble sausage and cheese in pie shell.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions in salted water for 5 minutes.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing and margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mixture on bottom of 9-inch pan.
Pour in vegetable mixture.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add moist ingredients and beat.
Bake in two greased and floured 8-inch layer round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for 1/4 cup butter and the crackers. Put into a greased casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top.
Pour on 1/4 cup butter.
Bake for one hour or until potatoes are tender at 350°.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Let rise.
Add butter and sugar, creamed; egg, well beaten; raisins, floured, and rest of cinnamon, salt and flour.
Knead.
Cover and let rise.
Shape, place on pan and cover again.
Let rise again.
Glaze with egg white diluted with water.
Cut a cross on top of each and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost across on each.

title: egg-cheese dish
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Trim crusts from bread, then butter.
Lay in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon over bread.
Combine eggs, milk, cheese, salt and pepper; pour over bread.
Let sit for 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until puffy and brown.

title: glazed spareribs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan: bring to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside.
Cut ribs into serving size pieces; place bone side up in a shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste ribs with sauce; turn over and bake 15 minutes.
Baste with sauce; turn again and bake 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: calico cake
directions: Follow directions on box of white cake mix as directed.
Divide batter into 6 smaller bowls.
Squirt drops of food coloring, making each bowl a different color until desired color is reached.
Leave 1 bowl white and add cocoa to make 1 bowl chocolate.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.

Drop teaspoonfuls of different color batter into both pans, being careful not to overlap same colors. Continue layers of colored batter on top being careful not to layer same color on top of each layer.
Bake according to box of cake mix.
Great for children's birthday parties.

title: green bean casserole
directions: After breaking beans, wash and drain.
Tightly pack beans in sterilized quart jars with lids.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to each jar. Pour hot water in each jar.
Tightly screw lids on jars.
Place quart jars in pressure canner, but not touching.
Add 2 quarts water for every 7 quarts to be cooked.
If less than 7 quarts are used, add a little more water.
Place lid on canner with 10 pounds pressure.
Cook on high for 20 minutes.
When first jingle starts, monitor heat to obtain 4 jingles per minute.
Do not open canner until steam is completely out of round pound weight or until canner is cool.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Drain and rinse beans; chop the onion, cilantro, bell pepper and red pepper.
Combine with beans; add lime juice, oil and vinegar; season and refrigerate.

title: christmas stollen
directions: Prepare roll mix as directed on the label, adding 1 egg and cardamon.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead in raisins.
Set aside 1/3 of the dough. Divide remaining dough in 3 equal parts and roll each in a strip about 12 inches long.
Braid.
Put on greased baking sheet. Divide other piece of dough into 3 equal parts and roll each into a strip about 10 inches long.
Braid.
Place smaller braid on top of larger braid.

title: chicken 'n biscuit bake
directions: In large skillet, combine 2 tablespoons margarine, chicken, onion, celery and pimento.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly, then separate biscuits into 10 biscuits.
Press biscuits over sides and bottom of pie pan.
Spoon chicken mixture over biscuits.
Bake 8 to 13 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Blend.
Spread onto a greased pan about 17 x 11 x 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Combine ingredients for 1 minute at low speed, then 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out.
Prick with fork.
Pour or brush on mixture of 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 cup Kahlua.

title: honey nut white fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in heavy medium saucepan. Bring to full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes, constantly stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, 1 cup nuts and vanilla. Stir vigorously for 1 minute, until marshmallows are melted. Pour into 9-inch foil-lined pan.
Chop remaining nuts; sprinkle on fudge and press in.
Chill.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage and dice scallions.
Mix.
Add sunflower seeds and almonds.
Crunch up noodles by hand.
Add to salad.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
In separate bowl, mix other 3 ingredients.
Put 1/2 second mixture in with first mixture. Keep 1/2 for icing.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: cheese cake
directions: Sift confectioners sugar and graham cracker crumbs together. Add 1 teaspoon of melted butter.
Press onto spring-form pan.

title: no fuss sweet rolls
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Let rise 2 times. Cut dough in half. Roll each half out on floured board into a rectangular shape.
Spread cinnamon on top.
Roll up and cut into 12 slices each. Pour melted butter or margarine in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cover with brown sugar, approximately 1 cup. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.
Place cut slices on top.
Let rise and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Makes 2 pans of sweet rolls.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown steak which has been cut into serving pieces.
Add onions and peppers.
While meat is browning, cook noodles.
After meat is done, put all the ingredients together.
Add as much bouillon, salt and pepper to taste.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Stir mustard into yogurt in a small bowl.
Gently stir in cucumbers.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve cold.

title: happiness cake
directions: Combine patience, love and generosity with understanding.
Add laughter.
Sprinkle generosity with kindness.
Add plenty of faith; mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime.
Serve everyone you meet a slice or two everyday you meet.
Good for all gatherings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Measure cucumbers after slicing.
Slice peppers and bury in crushed ice 2 hours.
Drain.
Pour cucumbers in mixture.
Heat, then after they change color, put in jars and seal.

title: white house quick and easy gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and vinegar.
Pour mixture into your favorite mold.
Yield: 4 servings

title: lemon-raspberry muffins
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder & salt into a large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Stir together yogurt & next 3 ingredients. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened. Toss together 2 tablespoons flour & raspberries; fold into batter. Spoon into lightly greased muffin pans, filling two-thirds full. Combine remaining 2 tablespoons flour & 3 tablespoons sugar. Cut butter into mixture with a pastry blender or fork until crumbly. Spoon evenly over batter in muffin pans. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove muffins from pan immediately. Makes 1 dozen.

title: pancake mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in airtight containers. Makes 19 cups.

title: puttanesca(olive and anchovy pasta sauce)
directions: In a skillet, cook the garlic and the red pepper flakes in the oil over moderately low heat, stirring, for 20 seconds; stir in the parsley and cook the mixture for 10 seconds.
Add the tomatoes with the juice and cook the mixture over moderate heat for 1 minute.
Add the anchovies, the olives and the capers and cook the sauce, stirring, for 2 minutes.
In a kettle of boiling salted water, cook the pasta until it is al dente; drain it and
in a bowl, toss it with the sauce.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese. Serves 2 to 4.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Soften butter and mix with crumbs.
Place 1/2 of the mixture in bottom of a 15 x 19-inch pan.
Mix milk, sugar and Dream Whip together and beat until fluffy.
Add cream cheese and beat until thick.
Place 1/2 of cream cheese mixture over crumbs.
Add pie filling.
Spread remaining cream cheese mixture over filling and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: taco stuffed pasta shells
directions: Prepare pasta shells according to package directions; rinse & drain; set aside. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cook beef and drain. Add seasonings and water. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Add beans and 3/4 cup cheese; mix well. Spread 1/4 cup salsa over bottom of baking dish. Fill pasta shell with beef mixture. Spoon remaining salsa over shells. Cover with foil and bake for 40-45 minutes. Sprinkle with green onions and remaining cheese. Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: menudo
directions: In one gallon of water, cook the ox foot for 2 hours in a large pot.
Add tripe and hominy.
Boil until tender, about 2 hours.
Add onion, garlic, cilantro and salt to taste.
Simmer one hour.
Serve with hot flour tortillas or French rolls and butter.

title: instant fudge
directions: Grease 8-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, salt, margarine and milk in a large saucepan.
Boil mixture over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat, add chocolate chips. Stir until chocolate melts.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: super bowl chili
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add chili powder to taste.
Cook until thick and vegetables are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: real chili joint chili
directions: In a skillet, lightly toast the whole cumin, then crush with a rolling pin.
If you use ground cumin, do not toast.
Saute onion and garlic in a little vegetable oil until transparent.
In same skillet, add a little more oil and sear meat until it has a grayish color.
Put cumin, garlic, onion and meat in a large pot. Add paprika and chili powder.
Stir to mix all ingredients as you add water to cover.
Simmer for around 1 1/2 hours, adding salt to taste after the chili has cooked for a while.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring all the time.
Cook for the rolling boil 3 minutes.
Add the vanilla and peanut butter and beat with electric mixer until thick.
Pour in buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: mexican vegetable rice
directions: In a frying pan, heat oil over medium heat; add onion, garlic and rice.
Cook and stir until onion is limp and rice is opaque. Stir in salt, cayenne and bouillon cubes, dissolved in boiling water.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Add peas and tomatoes and stir about 3 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: summer or zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes. Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream; stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mixture and butter.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture in bottom of casserole dish (greased); spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: country style pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with seasonings and brown in skillet.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup, water and onions.
Pour over chops; cover and bake at 350° until very tender.
To brown chops a bit, uncover the last 15 to 20 minutes.

title: backyard burgers
directions: Mix ground beef and ingredients thoroughly.
Press into (12) 1/4 pound hamburger patties.
Grill over charcoal until well done. Season with salt and pepper to desired taste.
Serve on your favorite buns with a slice of cheese and onion on the side.

title: coconut-honey fruit dip
directions: Place cottage cheese into blender or food processor.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Stir in honey, yogurt, coconut and orange peel until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown meat and vegetables.
Add rest in 3-quart casserole (except noodles).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Serve over chow mein noodles with more soy sauce to taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash.
Drain and mash.
Mix all ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat 1 1/3 cups sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt; stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full boil.
Continue stirring and cooking for 2 minutes.
Cool. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to custard; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla, rum flavoring and spices.
Add 8 cups remaining milk; chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: If broccoli is not tender, cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain; cut up. Combine all salad ingredients.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix beans with seasoning and mayo.
Line pan with bean mixture, then sour cream and then layer tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Take beans and put into large pan.
Add brown sugar and molasses and mix well.
Add onion, mustard and ham.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 250°
for another 1 1/2 hours.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add coconut and flour mixture to the egg mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 rolls and chill.
Cut and bake at 350°.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and Cool Whip together then mix all other ingredients together.
Chill overnight.

title: refrigerator rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar in saucepan.
Cook on low to medium heat, stirring constantly, until juice begins.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until mixture thickens.
If mixture is still too juicy, add another package of jello.
Pour into jelly jars and refrigerate.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel pears and grind and cook pears and sugar.
Then add coconut and pineapple, cook until thick.
Put in jars and seal with lids.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add boiling water.
Mix well and bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in a saucepan.
Heat to a boil, stirring once in awhile to keep from scorching.
Cook until a small soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat. Add margarine and peanut butter. Beat and pour into buttered dish. Cool.

title: yum yums
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg.
Add flour with soda, salt and baking powder.
Add rest of ingredients.
This recipe can be altered somewhat with different options, no salt, more or less chocolate chips, Rice Krispies, raisins and coconut to taste. Drop rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 100 delicious cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes, until golden.

title: taco macaroni salad
directions: Add taco seasoning to cooked meat.
Stir all ingredients together, except for the lettuce and meat.
Add these 2 just before serving, along with 1/2 cup or more (to your liking) French dressing (real red French, not creamy and not orange).

title: applesauce oatmeal cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Fold in applesauce, raisins, nuts and oats.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold two mixtures together. Bake 70 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large Ziploc bag.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into bag with crackers and shake until crackers are well coated. Store in an airtight container.

title: pork chops
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Flour, salt and pepper the pork chops and brown in hot shortening.
Drain off part of the shortening.
Slice the onion on top of the pork chops.
Add mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 soup can of water.
Stir and let simmer until tender.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add remaining ingredients. Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry cream cheese bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Press 3/4 of mixture into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes just until edges begin to brown.
Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Drop preserves by spoonfuls over cheese mixture.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes until set and edges are golden brown.
Cool before cutting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easter morning casserole(egg and cheese strata)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let sit in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken well done and debone.
Save your 2 cups chicken broth.
Fry corn tortillas in oil until stiff (don't overcook). Drain on paper towels.
Heat soup until hot and place in large mixing bowl.
Add the chicken broth and deboned chicken.
Mix well.
In a large oblong baking pan, put 1 layer tortillas, 1 layer chicken mixture and 1 layer thin sliced Velveeta cheese. Repeat until all mixture is gone (2 or 3 layers), ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 300° until bubbly hot.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough on a lightly floured surface into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle, brush with butter.

title: braised doves
directions: Roll doves in a dry mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown birds in a skillet with a small amount of shortening added.
Remove most of the drippings and add a small amount of water.
Simmer birds over low heat for 1 hour.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, celery and onions; add salt.
Let stand 4 hours; drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, turmeric and mustard seed. Bring to boil for 1 minute.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: butter pecan turtle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl combine crust ingredients, flour, sugar and butter.
Well mix ingredients until flour particles are fine.
Pat firmly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over unbaked crust.
Prepare caramel layer; pour evenly over unbaked crust. Bake near center of 350° oven for 18 to 22 minutes or until entire caramel layer is bubbly and crust is light golden brown.
Remove from oven. Immediately sprinkle with chips.
Allow chips to melt slightly (2 to 3 minutes).
Slightly swirl chips as they melt; leave some whole for a marbled effect.
Do not spread chips.
Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen bars.

title: red beans with rice
directions: Place all ingredients except the rice in a large kettle and simmer for 3 to 4 hours or until the gravy thickens.
Remove ham bone, garlic cloves, bay leaf and pepper pods before serving over rice.

title: cheeseburger and shells
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet; pour out fat.
Add cheese soup and tomato soup; add water and pasta.
Heat to boiling.
Cook over medium heat until shells are done.
Stir often.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: b.l.t. dip
