directions: Cook bacon crisp.
Crumble into pieces.
Toast all slices of bread and cut into 1/4 or 1/2-inch size pieces.
Place on plate. Guests can take bread slices and dip into mixture.

title: southern fried rabbit(or:  the march hare)
directions: Cut rabbit in serving size pieces and soak in vinegar solution (1/2 cup vinegar, 2 tablespoons salt and 6 cups water) for about 3 hours.
Rinse thoroughly.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo until it forms a hard ball.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Beat as long as it will stir.
Drop or pour on wax paper or a buttered dish.

title: easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookware with oil (Pam).
Cut broccoli into strips; place in pan.
Cut chicken in half; lay pieces on top of broccoli.
Put Swiss cheese on top of chicken. Pour cream of mushroom soup over mixture.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: st. patty's punch
directions: Tint crushed pineapple with 4 drops of food coloring.
Mix lemonade, juices and pineapple.
Tint with remaining food coloring; pour on ice cubes in punch bowl.
Just before serving, stir in beer.

title: alice murphy's mushrooms
directions: Mix in large bowl or gallon jug.
Let set few days and then try and eat only one.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Stew vegetables 15 minutes.
When soft, add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook slowly about 1/2 hour or longer.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: party crescent squares
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and lay out flat on 9 x 12-inch baking sheet pan.
Arrange in pizza shape.
Bake at 300° for approximately 8 minutes or until slightly brown.
(Note:
Do not bake by package directions.)
Cool.

title: shrimp dip 2
directions: Soften cream cheese with lemon juice and sauces.
Beat until smooth.
Add onion, celery, mayonnaise and shrimp which has been chopped into 1/2 to 1-inch bits if large shrimp, or left whole if tiny shrimp.

title: corn spoonbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(I make mine in a 9 x 11-inch glass pan with a cushionaire cookie sheet underneath to ensure a moist bread.)

title: yellow squash pickle
directions: Wash and cut squash in slices.
Peel and cut onions into quarters, then slice very thin.
Add to squash.
Cover with an inch of water and add salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly. Bring remaining ingredients to boiling.
Pour over squash and onions.
Let stand 2 hours.
Bring all ingredients to boiling point and heat 5 minutes.
Pack into preheated jars.
Leave 1/8-inch headspace.
Adjust caps and process in water bath canner at simmer temperature for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Test seals.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease loaf pan, chop nuts and mash bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Cream for 1 1/2 minutes. Scrape bowl, add banana, sour cream, nuts and flour mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. When cool, crumble it. Chop broccoli and onion. Combine broccoli, pecans, raisins, onion and bacon. Separately blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make dressing. Pour dressing over salad and lightly toss. Serves 10 to 12.

title: caramel pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and condensed milk; fold in Cool Whip. Spread half into pie crust. Drizzle with half of the caramel topping. Combine coconut and pecans. Sprinkle half over the topping. Repeat layer. Chill or freeze until serving.

title: campfire supper
directions: Will need aluminum foil.

title: popcorn drops
directions: Place popcorn in food processor or food grinder.
Grind into kernel size pieces.
Beat egg whites into stiff peaks.
Add sugar replacement, beating until well blended.
Fold popcorn pieces into stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: aunt edith's cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Crumble graham crackers and mix with 1/2 cup melted margarine; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and lard.
Stir in beaten eggs and flavor.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish, potatoes, onions and ground beef.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup over top.
Bake covered at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt pearl's silver dollar pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, salt and soda.
Mix.
Add enough flour to make a thin batter.
Mix well.

title: zucchini squash onion bake
directions: Slice squash into spears or coins.
Arrange in an aluminum pan.
Top with onion slices, then tomatoes, salt, pepper and sprinkle with oregano.
Top with bacon slices.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes, then out and arrange cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and pour over crust.
Cook at 350° for about 25 minutes, until fluffy.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pineapple shrimp maui
directions: Mix drained pineapple with shrimp, celery and orange sections. Blend mayonnaise, curry powder, garlic salt and lime juice.
Toss salad with part of the dressing, passing the remaining dressing at serving time.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat with spices and drain the fat.
In a glass baking dish, start with a layer of meat.
Add a layer of 1/2 the onion, then a layer of half the tomatoes, then a layer of creamed corn, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat the layers once more ending with creamed corn.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from the oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Crush the tostados and cover the pie, then add another layer of cheese.
Bake for another 5 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: whole wheat scones
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and margarine in large mixing bowl and add milk and melted margarine.
Mix will be sticky.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In large bowl mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
To this mixture add cherry pie filling and nuts.
In separate bowl whip the whipping cream until light and fluffy. Fold the whip cream into the other mixture.
Put 1 cup of vanilla wafer crumbs in a oblong bowl.
Glass works well.
Pour mixture over the vanilla wafer crumbs and top with more crumbs.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: In a blender, cream the butter and cheese. Add ice water, then flour and seasonings. Chill.

title: macaroni and cheese and chili
directions: Fix macaroni and cheese dinner.
Add in black pepper and cayenne pepper.
Add other ingredients and spices to taste.

title: incredulada enchiladas
directions: In skillet, heat oil and saute green pepper and onion for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add beef and brown lightly.
Pour off excess fat; discard.
Stir in taco mix, water and 1/2 cup of taco sauce.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: butter cookies
directions: Put together in order given.
Pat out on cookie sheet.
Press 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans on top. Moisten top with unbeaten egg white.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm; let cool in pan.

title: nutty walnut drops
directions: Place butter and maple syrup in small saucepan over low heat. Just when butter melts, remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and lemon rind.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, wheat germ and walnuts.
Place buttermilk in cup and add maple syrup.
Stir until dissolved.
Add all ingredients together; stir until combined. Drop batter by the teaspoon onto lightly oiled baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: peanut butter roll(candy)
directions: Stir together confectioners sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mixture will need to be very stiff. Roll out until very thin on a floured or confectioners sugar covered area.
Spread thin layer of peanut butter over this and roll as a jelly roll.
Refrigerate until cold.
Slice

title: wyoming trout
directions: Fry bacon in frying pan.
Add vegetable oil, enough to give you 1/4-inch.
Salt and pepper trout; dip in milk, then roll in flour that has been salt and peppered.
Fry at a high heat for approximately 5 minutes per side, starting with skin down.
Serve with lemon or orange wedges.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In large frying pan, heat oil (medium high); slice tomatoes and roll in flour and meal mixture. Place in hot oil. After all tomatoes are rolled and in pan, cut up hot pepper over top and cook with lid on, stirring 2 or 3 times until done. Should come out crispy in places and kind of mushy in others.

title: bambinos
directions: Place Ritz crackers on ungreased cookie sheet.
Squeeze a small amount of Pizza Sauce on each cracker and spread over entire cracker surface with a spoon.
Sprinkle cheese and pepper over crackers.
Add other toppings and spices as desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5-10 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: chocolate cheese cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin tins with paper cups.
Make cake mix as directed.
Spoon batter into pans 2/3 full.

title: company apple pie
directions: Pare and cut apples into eighths.
Bring water, sugar, salt and cinnamon to a boil.
Add apples and simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Add cornstarch mixture quickly.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: oven crispy chicken
directions: Coat a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Put milk in a shallow dish.
Mix remaining ingredients (except chicken) in a bowl.
Dip each piece of chicken in milk, then in the bread crumb mixture for a coating.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat for 7 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken and roast together. Chop meats up.
Mix cream-style corn, potatoes, Worcestershire sauce and apples together. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes about 4 gallons.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Tear into pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble into bits.
Add vinegar to fat in pan, along with water and brown sugar.
Salt and pepper liquid.
Heat to boiling point.
Add bacon bits and pour hot dressing over the lettuce.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Peel and slice (thin) potatoes.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with potato slices.
Top with hamburger meat and then beans.
Top with bacon slices and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until potatoes are done.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake additional 5 minutes, until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: lentil soup (winter soup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Stir to boil.
Cook 30 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Precook 1 (9-inch) pie crust as directed.
Boil chicken until brown.
Drain. Shred chicken into chunks.
Add cream of chicken soup and vegetables.
Cook until hot.
Pour into cooked pie crust. Use remaining pie crust to make topping layer.
Cook at temperature given on pie crust.
Cook until brown.

title: country spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup ring mold or Bundt pan.
Measure flour and remaining ingredients into large mixing bowl.
With mixer on low speed, beat well until blended. Turn into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack. Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.

title: california vegetable pie
directions: Brown
beef
and onion, then drain.
Saute zucchini and green pepper
in oleo for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in dill seed.
Separate
dough
into
triangles
and
press into bottom of	a 9-inch ungreased pie plate to form crust.
Spoon in
meat mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Cheddar over meat.
Spread zucchini, green pepper and
dill over meat and top with tomato slices. Bake 10 minutes
at
375°.	Take
out
of
oven
and sprinkle remaining cheese
over
tomatoes
and bake 15 minutes more.

title: marbled chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all well. Can use either a preheated iron skillet or preheated muffin tin. This will make 12 muffins. Wonderful with dried beans. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: judy's dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda and egg; mix until blended.
Stir in softened yeast.
Gradually add flour to form soft dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place for about 1 hour.
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole, 1 to 1 1/2-quart size.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Brush with additional butter; cut in wedges to serve.
One serving contains 181 calories and 3 gm fat.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower according to directions on package; drain. Combine all ingredients, except chives, in blender; blend until smooth.
Add chives; heat well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in large bowl. Add grated cheese and mix. Add remaining ingredients (except pecans) and mix well. Shape into 1 large ball. Chill until nearly firm. Take out; roll in pecans. Wrap in foil and refrigerate. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.

title: "mama's" pound cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure and add baking powder and salt. Sift three times.
Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Cream together until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour (small
amounts at a time).
Beat on high for several minutes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad with poppy seed dressing
directions: Break spinach leaves into large salad bowl.
Add sliced boiled eggs; bacon strips broken into small pieces, sliced mushrooms and onions/scallions cut into small pieces.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill until just before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and toss to mix well. Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: ham asparagus shortcake
directions: Mix and heat mixture.
Put in between and on top of 6 biscuits.
One box of biscuit mix makes 6 biscuits.
Can save center slices of eggs to garnish top of biscuits.

title: grandma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and egg, beating until fluffy.
Stir in baking powder and salt.
Blend in flour.
Mix until a stiff dough forms.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork (dip fork in sugar to keep from sticking) crisscrossing to flatten. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Roll in chopped pecans, paprika, parsley or chili powder.

title: coconut snow cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Add coconut pecan icing and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir well.
Bake in 2 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely. Ice with whipped cream and top with coconut.

title: texas style beef brisket and barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 10 to 12 pounds whole (untrimmed) beef brisket in low oven for several hours (3 to 4) until very tender.
(We use a Brown-N-Bag or cover with foil.)
Put cooked meat on low temperature.
Grill with lots of mesquite (hickory will do, barely) wood for smoke.
Baste with barbecue sauce every 15 minutes for 2 to 4 hours (this drives the neighbors crazy!).
Sauce is good for chicken, too.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Chopped nuts may be added if desired.

title: fruity macaroon cookies
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Sift flour, powder and soda together; add to first mixture.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; drop by level tablespoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries and put them and apple and orange through a food grinder.
Add sugar, nuts and celery.
Do not run nuts and celery through grinder.
Do not use directions on jello box but use the listed amount of water, 1/2 hot and 1/2 cold.
Stir jello until a little thick.
When partially set, add other ingredients and put in a mold or dish.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook almonds on cookie sheet until brown (about 10 minutes).
Finely chop almonds to fine powder; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and extracts; blend good.
Gradually add flour, salt and nuts.
Put in pastry bag or spoon out, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: pork chops a la jenni
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour and shake off excess.
Brown chops on both sides in butter in a large skillet. Then place in overlapping rows in a shallow casserole or baking dish.
Spoon pan drippings and mushroom soup over chops.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake covered in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad pockets
directions: In medium bowl, combine chicken, celery, raisins and green onions.
In small bowl, combine mayo, lemon juice and ginger; blend well.

Pour dressing over chicken mixture; mix well. Arrange 1/4 of spinach leaves and 1/4 of apple slices in each pocket with the pieces extending slightly over edge of pocket. Spoon 1/4 of chicken salad mixture into each pocket.
Makes 4. Calories:
Fat:
8 gr.
Sat. Fat:
1 gr.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Let stand 10 minutes so liquid raises to top and remove liquid.
Stir in eggs and other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a hot well-greased skillet. Brown on both sides, drain on paper towel.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: mom's boiled custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Pour into skillet; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl; cover with waxed paper and place lid on top.
Serve cold over chocolate layer cake.

title: no fuss caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large brown paper bag and set aside. Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in bowl and microwave 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute until mixture comes to boil. Microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over corn in the bag, close bag 3 or 4 rolls and shake well.
Place bag in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes, then shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 more minutes, then shake.
Pour out on large pan or cookie sheet and mix it up.
Very good.
Have patience microwaving, it's worth it.

title: crisp pecan cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add egg yolk, 1/2 cup pecans, vanilla, cinnamon and flour. You will have to use your hands after flour is added. Pat dough in well-greased cookie pan 1/4-inch deep. Brush with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle the rest of pecans and pat down. Bake 20 minutes in preheated 375° oven. This recipe can be cut in squares when baked.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Boil and drain noodles.
Brown onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add flour and stir until mixed.
Add clam juice, clams and chicken broth.
Simmer until slightly thick.
Pour over drained noodles.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Toss lightly.

title: chunk ham succotash
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Add onion and cook slowly for three minutes.
Stir in corn, chopped pepper, beans, milk and half and half.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add ham, cook for 5 minutes, or until thick. Season with pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In saucepan, add oregano, salt, pepper and garlic to water. Bring to boil.
Add tomato sauce.
Stir.
Add sugar and stir for 1 minute.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Filling:
Combine sour cream, sugar, 1 1/2 cups coconut and vanilla; mix well.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add about one tablespoon sugar. Set aside.
In large bowl, put milk, sugar, salt, egg and shortening (stir well).
Add flour.
Knead dough about 5 minutes. Let rise 1 hour.

title: mint cookies
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Dip each cracker in melted mixture. Set on wax paper to harden.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Dump in cherries and pineapple. Spread over pan. Spread dry cake mix evenly over mixture. Daub mixture with butter. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix all together; put into a baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours.
Yields 6 to 12 servings.

title: vegetable batter(for deep frying)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Beat egg white and fold into mixture.
Fry dipped vegetables at 400°.
(Banana peppers have to be parboiled.
Zucchini squash is good when fixed this way.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: american-style lasagna
directions: In a glass bowl, crumble the beef and add the garlic.
Cover with paper toweling.
Microwave on High power until meat is no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Drain off any fat.
Add the sauce, herbs and water.
Return to the microwave.
Microwave 5 minutes on High power, stirring once, until sauce is hot.

title: muscatrolle
directions: Slowly fry onions in butter.
Add meat.
Cook shells and drain.
Mix shells, mushrooms and tomato soup with meat and onions.
Add a little water, if necessary.
Mix in cheese and simmer slowly until melted.
This recipe makes a large casserole.

title: frozen slush
directions: Blend in blender.
Serve as "slush" type drink.
Cooling. Decorate with orange, lime or lemon slices and cherries, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
In saucepan, over medium heat, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup and cream cheese, stirring constantly until smooth and hot.
In casserole, alternately layer frozen potatoes and hot sauce, ending with a sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix corn and egg.
Add to dry ingredients stirring lightly.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry about 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 16 fritters.
Make sure to fry only a few at a time.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Cook in boiling water for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain and mash.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish and store in the refrigerator.
When you are ready, dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak tomato skewers
directions: Allow 1/4 pound ground beef per serving.
Season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and pinch of thyme.
Shape into 3 meatballs.
On skewers, alternate meatballs and 2 pimiento stuffed olives.
Cook over hot coals until desired doneness.

title: bacon turnovers
directions: Make dough and roll a portion out to a 5 inch circle.
Put a portion of the filling in the center.
Brush with water to seal. Crimp edges and brush with beaten egg.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top cookies with sugar/cinnamon mixture.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage with fennel seed, onions, red pepper and garlic salt.
Drain well.
Thaw and roll out dough until thin.
Sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese on dough.
Roll up as a jelly roll.
Bake on greased 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits and reserve juice.
Mix pudding according to pkg. directions using fruit juices instead of milk.
Mix cool whip with pudding and add this mixture to fruits.

title: quiche
directions: Melt cheese in hot milk.
Crumble cooked bacon or shaved ham into unbaked pie shell.
Add eggs, salt and pepper to milk and cheese mixture.
Pour over bacon into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes, then bake at 300° about 35 minutes.
Best served hot.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in a large bowl with wire whisk the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk, sugar and Cool Whip. Spread in crust.
Mix pudding and 1 cup milk together with wire whisk.
Beat for 1 or 2 minutes. Stir in pumpkin.
Add cinnamon, ginger and cloves. Spread mixture over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Bring the tomatoes and sugar to a boil for 1 minute.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add clams, juice and parsley; simmer.
Pour over linguini.
Serves 1.
Each serving provides 2FA, 3P, 2B, 1PS (B).

title: pink wedding punch
directions: Clean, slice and sweeten strawberries.
Mix lemonade and water.
Combine with strawberries.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, add sparkling water and champagne and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Yields 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns. Combine next 7 ingredients. Mix with hash browns. Put all in 3-quart casserole dish. Saut cornflakes in 1/4 cup melted butter and sprinkle on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: muscadine custard
directions: Chop
hulls
slightly.	Blend
sugar, flour, eggs, milk, butter and mix with
hulls.
Pour
into
a	9-inch	unbaked pie crust and bake until
knife
inserted into pie comes out clean. May use top crust if desired.
Dot top crust with butter.
Bake in 350° oven until brown for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower-broccoli toss
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into pieces, wash and set aside to drain.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli and green onions and toss.
Combine remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and chill overnight before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs with whip or spoon.
Add other ingredients.
Cook in unbaked pie shell 10 minutes at 400°.
Turn down heat to 325° and cook for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix pudding mix according to directions on box.
Add Cool Whip.
Line sheet cake pan with crackers. Add pudding mix.
Top with graham crackers. Add frosting on top. Refrigerate.

title: microwave gingerbread
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed. Then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Shield corners.
Microwave at 50% for 6 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Remove foil.
Increase power to High.
Microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until done.
Cool. Serve with whipped topping.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Add onion to hamburger.
Mash up tomatoes and add one can of water.
Combine the remaining ingredients and cook until done. Add can of water if too thick.
Serve with corn bread.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Fry beef; drain grease.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of pan (for 2, use 2 pie plates; for 1, use 10 x 10-inch pan), then layer following in order: ground beef mixture, chili peppers, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with taco chips.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Combine rice mix and water in saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir in 2/3 cup French fried onions, vegetables and cheese. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup onions over rice just before serving.

title: onion casserole
directions: Boil onions until almost done; drain.
Place onions in the bottom of a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle eggs over onions. Pour soup over eggs.
Mix butter and bread crumbs.
Put on top of eggs.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, 1/2 cup of sugar and melted margarine. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: jay leno's uncle louie's chicken wings marinara
directions: Cook chicken wings by broiling or lightly flour them and deep fry in safflower or peanut oil. While they are cooking, prepare the sauce.

title: crab patties
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Melt butter and cheese in microwave safe bowl.
Add crabmeat, mayo, garlic salt and season all.
Mix well.
I also salt and pepper this mixture.
Spread mixture on english muffins and bake until lightly brown on top.

title: honey kissed carrots
directions: Combine carrots and water in a medium saucepan; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat an additional 10 minutes or until carrots are glazed, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate-butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, eggs, vanilla and shortening.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a lot of cookies.

title: icebox strawberry dessert
directions: Place angel food cake (cubed) in bottom of large, rectangular pan, 2 inches deep.
Mix vanilla pudding, milk and ice cream. Spread over cake.
Mix jello and hot water.
Add frozen strawberries.
When mixed, pour over other mixture and refrigerate. Ready to serve when jello sets.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Toss ingredients 1 hour before serving.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup flour.
Add extract, the raisins and pecans that have been mixed with reserved flour.
Bake three hours at 250°.
Place pan of water under cake pan in oven.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and mushrooms; add to other ingredients and cook for 5 min on med heat.
Do not over cook.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds in a casserole.
Place in 375° oven until bubbly.
Place almonds on top of mixture and slide under broiler until brown.

title: baked pinto beans
directions: In large baking pan, add cooked beans, chopped onions, hot green peppers and quartered tomatoes. Season to taste with salt. Add liquid if necessary. Top with sliced bacon and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: rhubarb pizza
directions: Mix together the crust ingredients and pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: coconut butter balls
directions: Mix well together.
Roll in balls; roll in coconut. Refrigerate.

title: krystal's keep in shape grapefruit
directions: Cut the grapefruit in half.
Loosen fruit from skin, then cut each section close to the membrane.
Remove the core.
Dot each half with butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a bowl and sprinkle it over the grapefruit halves.
Put them on the broiler rack 4 inches from the heat.
cook for 8 minutes.
Decorate with maraschino cherries.
Serves 2.

title: old-fashioned pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Reserve pineapple juice; add enough milk to make 1 cup.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil water and cook rotini until tender; drain.
In a bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups Miracle Whip and Italian dressing until smooth, creamy and thick.
If too thick, add a small amount of Italian dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with parsley flakes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla, then all other ingredients, leaving raisins and nuts until last.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti and cook per package directions.
Drain.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Saute mushrooms and onions in margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over spaghetti, but don't mix.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mexican one dish meal
directions: Brown ground meat and rice together.
Add chopped onion and bell peppers.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing in order given. Put in casserole.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend flour, soda, sugar, salt and cinnamon into bowl.
Add this dry mixture to the eggs, oil and zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in a greased loaf pan.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: You will also need an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and egg yolks until fluffy. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Set aside. Butter 48 miniature muffin cups; sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs (dump out excess).
Fill tins with mixture and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until set.
Place about 1/2 teaspoon of cooked topping on each cake.
May top each cake with favorite pie filling or fruit.

title: gordon's mother's cheese cake
directions: Blend butter with sugar and crumbs.
Press into spring-form pan (my pan is 8 1/2-inches, but you can use 8 or 9-inch and adjust the cooking time a little).
Stir cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
With electric mixer, blend 1 minute.
Then add unbeaten egg yolks and stir only enough to blend.
Stir in sour cream, vanilla and lemon juice.
Fold in beaten stiff egg whites.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven. Leave pan in 1 more hour.
Open oven door, leave pan in 1/2 hour longer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup cheese to meat.
Seed peppers and boil in lightly salted water 5 minutes.
Drain and stuff with meat mixture.
Place in casserole.
Put any extra meat around the peppers.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt cheese in soup.
Add pimentos and 1 tablespoon oleo. Spray casserole dish with spray.
Pat 1/2 asparagus in bottom. Slice 2 eggs over top, then half of soup-cheese mixture and half of cracker crumbs.
Repeat for next layer.
Dot with oleo and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: pizza dough(for one 11 x 14 rectangle)
directions: Sprinkle yeast
and
sugar
into
very
warm water in a large bowl.
Stir until well blended and allow to stand for 10 minutes. Stir flour and salt into bowl until a stiff dough is formed.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured pastry cloth or board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes, using only enough flour
to
keep
dough from sticking.
Place in a large greased bowl;
cover,
let rise 30 minutes.
Punch down dough.
Grease hands and cookie sheet lightly.
Place dough on pan and stretch with hands to form crust.
Leave edge slightly thicker.
(Apply toppings, bake at 400°, for 40 minutes.)

title: garlic chicken pizza
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
In a large bowl, combine half of the green onion, the garlic, vinegar, soy sauce, first tablespoon oil, red and black peppers.
Add chicken; stir to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.
Drain, reserving marinade.

title: eastern shore chicken
directions: Place washed chicken in microwavable dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over chicken.
Microwave chicken on High, covered, for 20 minutes, rotating after 10 minutes.
Then grill for 8 minutes on each side over medium-hot to hot grill.

title: oat burgers
directions: Boil all ingredients together except oats and soy sauce.
Stir in oats and soy sauce and bring to boil again.
Turn off heat. Form into patties and brown in oil-rubbed frypan about 12 minutes on each side.
Serve with mushroom gravy or tomato sauce.
Garnish with parsley or onion rings.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cut butter into flour mixture; add eggs alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well after each addition; add almond flavoring and beat.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour, then turn to 350° for 1/2 hour.
DO NOT open oven door while baking.

title: beefy-beany-macaroni and chili
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add other ingredients, except cheese. Cover; simmer for 12 to 15 minutes, or until macaroni is tender. Add cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix in melted margarine and sugar. Press in bottom of pie pan.
Soften ice cream and mix in peanut butter.
Pour into crust and freeze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Combine chocolate and butter or margarine; beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar and continue to beat.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Beat for 1 minute.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and stir into chocolate mixture.
Stir in applesauce, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Put in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: grandma's boston cookies
directions: Mix and cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon; mix together.
Stir in cooked and drained raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Put cake mix into a bowl and cut in margarine.
Add 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Spread half the mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes. Melt caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cover baked layer with chocolate chips and 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Spread caramel mixture over chips and nuts.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with mixture until smooth.
Spoon into a greased, 2-quart, shallow casserole dish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl, mix at high speed until smooth.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Serve with fruit.

title: west meets east soup
directions: Set aside seasonings from soup mix.
Sort and discard foreign matter from beans.
Rinse beans and place in a 5 to 6-quart pan. Add 2 1/2 quarts water. Let stand at least 8 hours or overnight; drain and rinse.

title: grape jam
directions: Pulp the grapes, saving the skins.
Put the pulp on to cook with a small amount of water to keep it from sticking.
When soft mixture, rub through sieve to remove the seeds.
Add the skins after you have put them through a blender.
Add 3/4 pound of sugar for each pound of grapes.
Cook until mixture is thick or test a little on a cold plate.
Seal in sterilized glass jars.

title: broccoli, cauliflower and carrots
directions: Cook vegetable mix until done.
Drain.
Put in pan and slice Velveeta cheese and put on top of vegetables.
Melt 1/2 cube oleo and mix with 1 tube of crushed Hi-Ho crackers.
Put on top of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbles.

title: soft dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add butter, sugar and salt in milk; when lukewarm, add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add egg, slightly beaten.
Stir in the flour gradually and form into a soft dough.
Knead 2 minutes.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size.
Shape into rolls; let rise again.
Bake until golden brown.
Remove from oven and brush tops with melted butter if desired.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: sauerkraut("easy and the best")
directions: Prepare cabbage and pack in quart jar. Add ingredients and cover with boiling water. Leave an inch at top of jar. Seal and store in cool place. Will be ready for use after 3 weeks.

title: cranberry wine spritzer
directions: Combine juice and wine in a pitcher.
Mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, stir in mineral water. Serves 4. Great over crushed ice.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer the
ingredients	in
order given (lettuce, peas, celery, green onions
and
bacon) in a shallow baking dish and then ice with mayonnaise or salad dressing, as you would ice a cake, being careful
to seal all edges.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: failproof custard
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat lightly.
Pour into custard cups.
Place in a pan of water and bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Brown stew beef in shortening in pot.
Add all ingredients except green peppers.
Simmer covered 2 hours.
Last 1/2 hour before done add green peppers.
Serve with brown rice or mashed potato.

title: whole meal deal
directions: Put cut sausage in a large pot with a tight lid.
Put all other vegetables in layers on top of sausage.
Salt and pepper each layer of vegetables, then put cut cabbage on top.
Add one cup of water.
Steam for 45 minutes to 1 hour (do not peek while the recipe is cooking).
Serve with corn bread.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Spread meat in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread peas over meat.
Combine potatoes and mushroom soup; spread over peas.
Cover potatoes with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: no knead herb bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Put margarine, sugar and all herbs in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over them and stir. Let cool.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 1 minute.
Stir in yeast and eggs.
Add about 1 3/4 cups flour to make a stiff batter.
Beat 1 minute.
(Dough will be soft.)
Cover lightly, put in a warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Grease 2 small or 1 large bread pan.
Stir down dough and place in pan.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Sweet 'N Low and cabbage.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Sweet 'N Low.
Pour over cabbage.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours.
Will keep 2 to 4 weeks in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: chix picante
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Dredge in flour and saute in a heavy skillet over high heat with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Cook for about 3 minutes on each side or until just done. Set aside and keep warm.

title: baked peas
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and cook until crisp.
Make white sauce of milk, flour and butter.
Add peas, salt, pepper and bacon.
Put in greased casserole and cover with bread crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: baked brie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Let pastry sheet come to room temperature.
Roll pastry out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out circle 8 to 9-inches in diameter.
Place cheese in center of pastry, wrapping pastry around cheese and pinching edges to seal.
Decorate pastry case with scraps of pastry cut in various shapes.
Place pastry on ungreased baking sheet and immediately reduce oven temperature to 400°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Serve with crackers or fresh sliced apples or pears.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, the cinnamon and 1/2 cup of the walnuts. Place apples in bottom of a greased 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cinnamon mixture.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain; mix flour with small amount of milk until creamy.
Add the rest of the milk, salt, pepper and butter to potatoes.
Bring to a boil; add flour.
Cook until thick.

title: chicken with buttermilk dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, onion and enough water to cover in a large pan; cook until tender.
Remove chicken from broth, reserving broth.
Debone chicken.
Sift flour, soda and salt together into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Blend egg and buttermilk.
Stir enough buttermilk mixture to form dough.
Roll thin on lightly floured board.
Cut into short strips.
Combine chicken, soup and broth; bring to a rolling boil, stirring.
Drop in dumplings and cook until tender.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine; add flour to make paste.
Add broth slowly. Add vegetables.
Simmer covered for approximately 45 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.
Add milk.
Simmer uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: caribbean black beans and brown rice
directions: *Can substitute a 16-ounce can of Italian tomatoes, chopped.

title: quick and easy sheet cake
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour into a well-greased 10 x 15-inch sheet cake pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Just before cake is finished baking, make following topping.

title: potato peel snacks
directions: Deep fry potato peels until golden brown.
Place cheese over peels while hot.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon or bacon bits on top. Let melt.
Make sure peels are thick and 4 to 5 inches long.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to boil.
Place oil, onion, salt and mustard in blender.
While blending, slowly add sugar/vinegar mixture through top.
Blend on low speed 30 seconds.
Stir poppy seed into dressing and chill.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: cold corn salad
directions: Pour liquid over corn; blend well.
Let set overnight.
When ready to serve, drain completely of liquid in a colander.
Serve cold.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for about 20 minutes.
Press through a sieve or food mill.
Melt butter and add remaining ingredients. Add tomatoes.
Heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Cooked rice or elbow macaroni may be added.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on box (2 round layers).
Crumble 1 round layer of cake mix in bottom of bowl.
Add a layer of strawberries, layer of pudding and layer of Cool Whip.
Place the 2nd round cake mix on top.
Add a layer of strawberries, pudding and layer of Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: easy chess cake
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat egg into margarine. Gradually add cake mix.
Mix well with a fork and press firmly into pan.

title: quick and easy salmon casserole
directions: Spread the mixed ingredients into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the top is slightly golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Measure all ingredients into large bowl.
Blend well for 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour. The longer this cake stands, the better the flavor.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as package directions. Mix with tuna, celery, onions, sour cream, mustard and salt. Layer in buttered casserole. Add 1/2 zucchini. Top with all cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add tomatoes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Use 2 heaping teaspoons to a cup of water.

title: banana cream cheese pie
directions: In mixing bowl combine cereal, sugar and margarine.
Press evenly and firmly in bottom and around sides of buttered 9-inch pan.
Chill.

title: aunt carole's crab spread
directions: Shape cream cheese into low flat circle.
Rinse crab meat and spread over cheese.
Chill.
Before serving, pour cocktail sauce over crab meat.
Serve with crackers.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions crosswise as thick as you wish; separate into rings.
Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add enough milk to make a thin paste mixture.
Dip onion rings and fry in hot oil until brown.
Serve immediately.

title: apricot pull-aparts
directions: Cut bread dough in half lengthwise.
Then cut each half crosswise into 8 pieces (16 pieces total).
Flatten pieces of dough with fingers, stretching slightly to form 4-inch circles of each circle.
Bring edges of dough together.
Pinch to seal.
In a small saucepan, melt the butter or margarine.
Dip filled rolls in melted butter or margarine, then in sugar.
Place, seam side down, in 2 layers in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until almost double (about 1 hour).
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, covering with foil the last 10 minutes of baking.
Remove from pan.

title: shortcut coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Place syrup and nuts in bottom of pan.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well. Separate biscuits.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then dip in sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in pan, spacing evenly. Sprinkle with remaining sugar and drizzle with remaining butter. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.
Cool upright in pan 5 minutes.
Then invert onto serving plate.

title: florida salad
directions: Drain all fruits thoroughly, about 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients; chill before serving.
Keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture, then stir in 1/2 cup candies and decorate cookies with the remainder of candy.
Preheat oven to 375° and place by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly brown.

title: white icing
directions: Beat well the oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add milk, flour and vanilla.
Beat well and frost your favorite cake.

title: coconut bread cubes
directions: Cut cubes of bread; dip in milk.
Roll in coconut and bake in slow oven until coconut is light golden brown.

title: coke chicken
directions: Melt margarine in electric skillet.
Place chicken in melted margarine, turning to coat both sides.
Pour Coke and ketchup over meat.
Cover pan and cook at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn chicken occasionally.
This makes a thick barbecue type sauce.

title: italian skillet supper
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, frozen vegetables with pasta, beans and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer uncovered for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables and pasta are tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 (1 1/4-cup) servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and sausage in skillet until done; drain.
Mix with pizza sauce.
Layer in baking dish the noodles, sauce and half of cheese.
Repeat layers again.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: fudge
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate pieces, beating until melted.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Put dry jello over cottage cheese and let set 5 minutes; stir together.
Add other ingredients and blend together with spoon. Refrigerate overnight, covered.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Place 6 slices of bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Add half the sausage and cheese. Repeat with remaining bread, sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Pour into pan.
Press into bread until evenly saturated. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Excellent for large crowd.
Can be prepared a day ahead.

title: zesty vegetable soup(cooking for one or two)
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, prepare soup as label directs, but add lemon juice and basil.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: hamburger buns
directions: In large
mixer
bowl,
combine 4 cups flour and yeast. Combine 2
cups
warm
water,
oil,
sugar
and
salt.
Add to mixture in
bowl;
add eggs.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 1/2 minute,
scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in 4 cups flour to make a soft dough.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo and cocoa together and set aside to cool.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Add to cocoa mixture.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into sheet pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans over top before baking.
Bake for 30 minutes.
As soon as cake is taken from oven, cover with marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows melt.
Let cool.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Whip cream cheese well. Add sugar & whip again. Mix in cool whip. Layer bananas in bottom of crust. Add cream cheese mixture. Top with pie filling. You can also use cherry or strawberry pie filling.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in buttered casserole.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bring to room temperature.
Cover top with thick layer of potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Makes large casserole.

title: praline candy
directions: Cook until soft balls drop in cold water.
Cool. Beat well. Drop on wax paper.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes.
Heat cream, cheese and butter or margarine until cheese melts.
Blend in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with sour cream and bacon bits.
Cook 10 minutes more or until bubbly.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon-honey chicken
directions: Dip chicken in beaten egg, then coat with flour.
Fry in olive oil for 10 minutes on each side.
While chicken is cooking, combine 1 tablespoon flour with cold water, stirring with wire whisk to prevent lumps and add rest of sauce ingredients.
Heat until sauce is thickened, stirring steadily.
Place cooked chicken in a serving dish and pour sauce over top.
Serve with rice.

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.

In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients. Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed. Add raisins (batter will be stiff). Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for
10 minutes or until firm.
Remove and cool on wire rack. Makes 2 dozen cookies. Contains 72 calories, 0 g fat and 0 g cholesterol.

title: chow-chow relish
directions: Ground tomatoes, peppers, onions and cabbage and put into a container with glaze on it.
Put a layer of salt over it and let stand overnight.
The next morning wash and be sure all salt is out of mixture.
Put back in container and put 7 lb. sugar, 3 Tbsp ground allspice and 3 Tbsp turmeric and enough white vinegar to stir where you can cook it.
Cook until tender and put in jars and seal.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time. Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Do not underbeat!
Sprinkle flour-powdered sugar mixture 1/4 cup at a time, folding just until mixture disappears.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Use an ungreased angel food pan. Cool upside down on a funnel or bottle.
Take out when completely cooled.

title: fat and skinny "french fries"
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into thick strips (the thicker the strips, the less oil they need to brown).
Cover the potatoes with cold water; let stand 1 hour.
Drain and blot dry.
Spread the potatoes in a nonstick jelly-roll pan; sprinkle with oil.
Shake the pan. Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 40 minutes or until potatoes are brown and tender.
Turn the strips several times during baking. Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Makes 8 servings at 100 calories each.

title: garden rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, omitting butter or margarine; cool.
Toss lightly with next 8 ingredients.
Cover; chill. Garnish with peanuts.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: orange-pineapple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil water and put in dates.
Turn down to simmer; cover and set aside.
Combine orange jam, pineapple, honey, egg whites and vanilla.
Remove dates from steaming water and mix with mixture.
Sift flours, soda and salt.
Add the orange mixture to the flour mixture.
Fill two bread loaf pans half full. Bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok; stir-fry meat.
Add vegetables; stir-fry.
Add seasoning mixture; stir-fry 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line bottom with 8 slices bread.
Cover with sliced chicken.
Spread slices with mayonnaise; sprinkle with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining 8 slices bread.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt; pour over entire casserole.
Refrigerate overnight or all day.
When ready to bake, spread soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven; bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 10.

title: chow mein
directions: Cut meat in small pieces (or have the butcher do it for you) and brown in Crisco or vegetable oil.
A frying pan works better than
a wok.
Add molasses, mustard, celery and onions.
Cover with water and cook 1 hour or until meat is done.
Add bean sprouts and thicken with cornstarch (put 1 tablespoon of cornstarch in 1/4 cup warm water; stir, then add to mixture).
Pour sauce over noodles and/or rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, Jell-O, water and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into bowl and chill until thickened.
Then blend in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Stir in 1 cup sliced strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until set, 1 to 2 hours. Garnish with additional Cool Whip and berries.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Flour and grease tube pan.
Pour into tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: good and easy pot-roast
directions: Put beer and flour into browning bag and mix.
Coat the bag with mixture.
Put pot-roast into bag.
Add peeled potatoes and sliced onion over the mixture.
Tie up the bag with tie.
Put 6 (1/2-inch) cuts into the browning bag.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cheeseless cheesecake
directions: Mix sour cream; add pudding mix, then add pineapple.
Chill in 9 x 12 inch pan.

title: beef 'n bean enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until onion is soft.
Add beans, salt, garlic powder, taco sauce and olives.
Heat until bubbly and set aside.

title: quick quiche
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain on paper towel.
Blend next 3 ingredients; stir in meat, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Insert knife and if it comes out clean, the quiche is done.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Cut off fat from chops as much as possible; use to grease skillet.
Brown chops in 1 teaspoon olive oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Season chops to taste.
Place thick slice of onion on each chop.
Pour 1 cup uncooked rice over all.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 pints stewed tomatoes.
Cover; simmer from 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock pot pintos
directions: Sort beans, discarding rocks and ugly beans.
Place in large bowl and cover with cool water 2-inches above beans.
Soak overnight.
After soaking, drain and rinse beans.
Place in crock pot.
Cover with cool water to about 2-inches above beans in pot. Add nothing else now!
Cover with lid and cook on high heat setting for 5 to 6 hours; the longer, the better.
Don't open lid. You should not have to add water during cooking, but if you do, add boiling water only.
About 1 hour before serving, saute seeded jalapeno, onion and garlic in bacon drippings only until tender. Add vegetables, bacon drippings and desired salt.
Re-cover and continue to cook on high for 1 more hour.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Combine with corned beef and remaining ingredients.

title: stew
directions: Brown stew meat in skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large Dutch oven. Bake, covered, 5 hours at 275°.
Serves 4.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Mix small amount of flour into fruit and nut mixture; toss to coat and set aside. Add remaining flour to egg mixture. Stir in flavoring. Fold in fruits and nuts. Bake at 225° for 2 hours.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onion and peppers.
Spread salt over the mixture and let stand overnight.
In large saucepan mix mustard seed, pickling spice, celery seed, turmeric and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove seed and spices by straining.
Add sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add squash mixture and bring to a boil, stirring often.
As soon as mixture has started boiling, put in hot jars and seal.
Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: pirate's pantry spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar; pour over rest of ingredients and mix well.
Make the day before you plan to serve the salad.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together
cake
mix,
melted
margarine and 2 eggs. Pat in the bottom of a "Pammed" sheet cake pan.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add next 4 ingredients, then add the last 4 ingredients.
Pour in aluminum tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake for 3 hours at 275°.
Half hour before cake is done, remove from oven and brush with honey or syrup.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until puffy and brown.

title: derkum's hamburger special
directions: Combine the hamburgers together in skillet and fry until brown, also adding onion and green pepper.
Then drain excess fat. Add sauce and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese until room temperature.
Blend in Ranch mix; add chicken.
Mold into a ball; roll in pecans.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Drain beans; reserve liquid. Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove enough grease to make 1/2 cup.
Add onions and cook until tender. Add brown sugar, catsup and mustard. Stir until well mixed. Add beans.
Cook until boiling. Turn flame down. Simmer 10 minutes. Crumble bacon and add.
Simmer another 10 minutes. Stir to prevent sticking. If sauce is too dry, add some juice that was drained off beans.

title: mexican corn
directions: Melt butter. Stir in cream cheese, corn and green chilies. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 9.

title: baked fillets
directions: Thaw fillets, if frozen.
Brush with salad oil; sprinkle lightly with the salt, then arrange in a buttered shallow baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar in bowl.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and pour into iron skillet.
Cook at 400° until golden brown for about 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour, salt and pepper steak.
Brown in a small amount of oil.
Add onions, celery, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Cook slightly.
Add tomatoes and water and cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: bernice's peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, blend peanut butter, sugar, eggs and baking soda with a spoon until smooth.
Do not beat.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for approximately 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Then, continue to cool on wax paper.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: In greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion. Combine remaining ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry yeast in warm water and let stand until dissolved. Sift flour and then sift together 4 cups of the flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Into this mix the cup of shortening.

title: *kadaifi 2
directions: In a large bowl, shred Kadaifi.
Use an 11 x 13-inch or 11-inch round pan.
Butter bottom and sides of pan.
Layer Kadaifi in pan. Sprinkle nut and sugar mixture over Kadaifi evenly. Sprinkle butter over layer and repeat this procedure until you finish with the last layer of Kadaifi and butter

title: banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Combine mashed bananas and cereal.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and pour in small casserole dish.
Heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly!
Serve hot with crackers.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Cook margarine, cocoa and water to a boil, then pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, then buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix the ground beef with the egg, onion and bread crumbs. Spread out on a large cookie sheet.
Top with the pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Delicious!

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: open face taco
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown ground beef and add tomato juice and the package of taco seasoning.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Separately cook cheese sauce; mix Cheddar cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
To serve, layer corn chips, rice and meat sauce.
Then add lettuce and top with cheese sauce.
Serve 4 to 6 people.

title: chicken ball
directions: Drain water off chicken.
Mix chicken and cream cheese in bowl.
Refrigerate for awhile.
Form into ball with spoon on plate or platter.
Serve with chicken-flavored crackers.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and pour into baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and spread over top of potato mixture. Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes.
May be prepared and frozen, ready to bake when needed.

title: mary's spinach salad
directions: Mix well in blender or shake in bottle.
This should have a sweet and sour taste.
Better if stored in fridge overnight. Shake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf salad plus
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and add the rest of the ingredients; toss lightly with salad dressing.

title: micro potatoes parmesan
directions: Melt butter in shallow 9-inch dish in microwave oven.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic; toss.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap; place in microwave oven on full power 5 minutes.
Stir in green pepper and salt; toss.
Cover and microwave on full power 3 minutes.
Gently mix in cheese.
Toss gently and dust with paprika; microwave on full power, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Let rest 2 minutes.
Sprinkle on parsley.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle with flour before putting sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° in sealed foil for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tasty guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet green tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables in meat grinder or food processor.
Mix with salt.
Put mixture in thin cloth bag; let drain overnight.
Next morning empty bag into large kettle, add sugar.
Stir mixture; add cider vinegar and pickling spices and let mixture boil for 20 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Fill canning jars which have been in a kettle of boiling water; seal filled jars.
Cover with lids which have been in boiling water.

title: nanny bread
directions: Add enough warm water to milk to make one quart.
Add the shortening, melted, to this.
Then add yeast cake and sugar to lukewarm water.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add salt to liquid.
Then add enough flour to make a dough stiff enough to knead.
Let rise until double, covered with a wet towel.
Knead again until light and springy.
Divide in 4 equal parts and shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans and let rise until light, not quite so much as double in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Rub in butter until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Add raisins.
Combine buttermilk, egg and baking soda.
Stir buttermilk mixture into flour; mix until moistened.
Bake in greased 1-quart pan or casserole in moderate oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Use knife to form cross on top of bread before putting in oven.

title: cheese cake supreme
directions: Combine the ingredients thoroughly and reserve 2 tablespoons. Press mixture firmly against the bottom and sides of a 10-inch head pan.
Pour in the filling and sprinkle with reserved zwieback mixture.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Pour over finely chopped vegetables.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: shrimp-scampi style
directions: Note:
I use the fresh chopped garlic in the jar from Tom Thumb.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Mix sugar and seasonings; pour over apples.
Stir well and put in a casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and put on top of apples.
Bake in a moderate oven about 40 minutes, until crumbs are brown and apples are bubbly.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Divide in half.
To half of batter add 1 stick margarine and 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well; pour into 10 x 14-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes only.
While baking, melt 1 stick of margarine.
When melted add the remaining Eagle Brand milk and 1 cup of pecans.
Take spoon and spoon caramel mixture over top of cake that is baked.
Pour remaining batter over top of this mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes only.

title: pepperidge farm chicken casserole
directions: Place 1/2 of the stuffing in the bottom of a 11 x 7-inch pan. Pour melted margarine over.
Add cubed chicken.
Mix sour cream with soup and spoon over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing. Slowly pour broth over casserole, allowing it to soak through to bottom.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add next 3 ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and softened butter.
Then add one more cup of flour and beat until smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Let rise until double, 50 to 60 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut onion up in chunks and shred cheese.
Cut tomato in bite-sized pieces.
In separate bowl add the can of cream of chicken soup and milk and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in hot oil for about five minutes until tender, keep stirring.
Stir in oregano, salt, chilies and sugar.
Simmer for 10 minutes, uncovered, keep stirring.

Add chicken and taco seasoning, stirring until chicken is almost done then add tomatoes stirring until done. Lightly toast flour tortillas over medium heat in aluminum skillet, cooking on each side for 10 to 15 seconds.
Remove and add meat mixture and roll up.
Place with the seam side down in narrow buttered casserole dish.
Top with the milk mixture and finally top all of this with the shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.
When you are ready to serve then add the sour cream on top.
Serves 4.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Wash chilies and remove strings and seeds.
Drain.
Grate cheeses separately.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place a layer of chilies, then Cheddar, then Jack.
Repeat 2 more times.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks and add milk, flour and salt.
Beat whites, then fold into yolk mixture.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add enchilada sauce and bake 1/2 hour more.
Put oven rack as far away from heat source as possible.
This stuff burns easily!
Serves 10 to 15.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash but do not peel tomatoes.
Cut in halves crosswise.
Mix flour, salt, sugar and pepper.
Roll tomatoes one at a time in flour.
Brown on both sides in hot bacon fat.
Remove to hot serving dish and keep warm.
Add evaporated milk to the same frying pan.
Boil slowly, stirring constantly until thick (about 2 minutes).
Pour over tomatoes.

title: pineapple tangy lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and rind.
Add cold water and sour cream.
Chill.

title: melting moments
directions: Sift together flour, cornstarch and powdered sugar.
Beat margarine until smooth; add vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls; flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dad's buttermilk pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, mix milk, oil and eggs. Then add dry ingredients. Cook on a hot griddle.

title: baked tuna-dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and divide evenly onto hot dog buns.
Wrap each filled bun in foil.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until thoroughly heated at 300°.

title: cold macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain and let stand until cooled. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Season to taste.
It's best to let salad cool for at least 1/2 hour to let seasonings set.

title: cherry cheese pizza
directions: Roll pastry in 14-inch circle; put in 12-inch pizza pan. Flute edges; prick.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Blend cheese and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into partially baked crust and bake for 10 minutes; cool.
Spread pie filling over cheese layer and chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: glazed calico cake
directions: In large bowl, mix first 6 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in carrots, coconut, nuts and pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 9-cup tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and prick with fork.
Meanwhile, prepare glaze.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine.
Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham dip
directions: Dice onions and beef.
Mix with softened cream cheese.
Add Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Better served at room temperature.
Good on crackers, celery, carrot sticks and with chips.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix water and jello, let cool.
Add fruit and let set.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use half of cake mixture and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. When done, add chocolate chips, chopped peanuts and caramel mixture.
Then cover with remaining batter and bake for 20 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix at medium speed cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and onion.
Add shrimp and beat at low speed until mixed.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: shake and bake roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in large chunks with skins left on. Wash potatoes real good; leave skins on.
Place all ingredients in plastic bag and shake.
Place potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes until brown.
Serve hot.

title: baked beef stew
directions: In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, water, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch or 3 qt. baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Serve in bowls.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: easy cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-cup ovenproof dish. Bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes or until dip is bubbly.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 20 minutes in sheet pan.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours before serving.

title: strawberry blossoms
directions: Set cream cheese aside to soften.
Remove stems from berries to form a flat base.
Place on cutting board, pointed end up.
With a sharp knife, carefully slice each berry in half vertically to within 1/4-inch of base.
Cut each half into 3 wedges to form 6 petals.
Pull petals apart slightly.

title: farina balls dumpling soup
directions: Bring broth and salt to a boil.
Slowly add farina, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and eggs. Add parsley.
Cool.
Drop by teaspoons into hot chicken or beef broth.
Simmer, covered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24 dumplings.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except cinnamon.
Mix well.
Mix 1/3 of dry ingredients with cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix until well coated.
Mix eggs and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Batter will be very stiff.
Add coated apples, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and tear into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing.
Put half of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Spread chicken over stuffing.
In a separate bowl, mix both cans of soup and 2 cups broth.
Pour over chicken and then cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir, chill and serve.

title: quick punch
directions: Mix punch and pineapple juice together. Pour back into cartons and freeze. Take out of freezer 2-3 hours before serving. When ready to serve, add one 2 liter bottle ginger ale.

title: el maklouba(middle-eastern dish)
directions: You will need a 3-pint nonstick or Teflon coated pot with a tight fitting lid.

title: banana slush
directions: Blend bananas in container or blender.
Combine bananas with sugar, water and juices.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 3 1/2-gallon containers.
Freeze.
Let thaw 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice.
Add oil, sugar and applesauce.
Mix well until blended.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and poultry seasoning. Dip first in milk, then in flour mixture. Dip again in milk, then again in flour mixture. Brown in canola oil.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large pot brown and drain ground beef.
Add all 6 cans of ingredients.
Stir in both packages of taco seasoning and ranch dressing.
