Bring soup to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries according to directions; add marshmallows and dissolve while hot.
Also add dissolved gelatin.
Add apples and nuts and mix.
Pour into long loaf pan and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaves or plain.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs.
Add the soda to the sour cream and stir into the cream mixture.
Sift the salt with the flour and add to the cream mixture.
Mash the bananas and add to the mixture.
Grease 2 loaf pans and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Brush with butter.
Enjoy.

title: barbecue chicken sandwiches
directions: Place chicken broth and barbecue sauce in slow cooker crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 to 5 hours.
Serve on hot, toasted hoagie rolls.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange dip
directions: Place ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Serve with fruit dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: dry mustard pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in clean jars.
Put a pinch of alum over cucumbers.
Put the rest of the ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the cucumbers.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch skillet, melt 1/2 cup butter. Add onion and cook over medium heat until tender (4 to 5 minutes). Remove from heat.
Stir in water, stuffing, walnuts and apple. Fill in pockets in pork chops with stuffing; secure with wooden picks.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Stir in the mashed bananas and nuts.
Add sifted flour with salt, soda and baking powder alternately with the milk.
Bake in well-greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: christmas cake or raisin cake
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes; cool. After mixture cools, add last 4 ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased pan for 35 minutes (or until done) at 350°.

title: caramel biscuit ring
directions: Heat until butter melts.
Separate 2 cans of refrigerated biscuits.
Cut each into 4 pieces.
Place in a large bowl.
Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuit pieces.
Toss to mix.
Spoon biscuits into a greased ring pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°. Let stand 3 minutes and invert on plate.

title: tuna treat sandwiches
directions: Mix well all ingredients and place on a small bun. Wrap individually in foil and warm in oven at 175° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake in three layer at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together; blend well on medium-high speed.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: tofu pumpkin pie
directions: Blend tofu in a food processor or blender until real creamy and smooth.
Add brown sugar, pumpkin, egg whites and spices. Blend well.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake approximately 1 hour in a preheated 400° oven or until a toothpick inserted in center comes almost clean.
Cool and serve.
Serves 10.

title: chicken marinara
directions: In a nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray, cook chicken for 6 minutes on each side; remove and keep warm. Add mushrooms, garlic, basil and Italian seasoning to skillet; saute until mushrooms are tender. Stir in spaghetti sauce and wine or broth. Add chicken; cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until heated through. Serve over pasta.

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Bake potatoes for 15 minutes in oven at 325°.
Boil remaining ingredients for 5 minutes in saucepan, stirring continuously. Pour over yams, bake 15 minutes longer, basting frequently.

title: mardi gras beef broil
directions: Sprinkle meat with 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Broil until cooked as desired, turning once.
In skillet, cook onion, green pepper, herb and remaining garlic powder in oil until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Drain tomatoes, reserving juice.
Combine juice and cornstarch.
Add to vegetables.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add tomatoes, heat through.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Thinly slice meat; top with vegetables.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Can be served from a round loaf of pumpernickel bread that has had center removed.
Cut center into pieces to be used for spreading of dip.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries.
Heat and mix with jello.
Add cream cheese.
Mix well.
Set aside and cool.
Add Coke, pineapple and cherries.
Pour into dish and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch dish or similar, spread cream cheese on bottom; smooth to cover pan.
Place sliced peppers on cream cheese and press down.
Pour chili over cheese and peppers.
Sprinkle other cheeses over top.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with your favorite corn chips.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: *Note:
May substitute 3 cups sliced fresh peaches for pineapple.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients in a 4-cup Pyrex pitcher. Microwave for 4 minutes. Stir real good.
Microwave for 3 1/2 minutes. Add the vanilla and add the butter.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Add the soda.
Stir and pour quickly onto buttered cookie sheet. After 30 minutes, turn the candy over to let it dry thoroughly. Break into bite size pieces and enjoy.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in margarine.
Cover completely in cracker crumbs. (Ziploc bags work well to "shake.")
Cover all with generous coating of cheese.
Bake at 350° until juice from chicken runs clean.
Easy and delicious.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: Serve with tortillas (I use wheat), chopped, diced tomatoes, cheese, peppers, sour cream, etc.
Cut bone away from turkey breast, then slice breast so that you end up with strips of turkey.
Mix fajita marinade (usually with vinegar, oil and water) and soak turkey strips in marinade.
Slice bell pepper and onions into strips; slice garlic.
Heat oil in large pan; put in garlic slices and then pepper and onions.
Sprinkle to taste with chili powder and Cajun seasoning.
Cook to taste (I like mine still with a bit of crispness).
In another frying pan, heat oil; add in some of the marinade and cook strips of turkey (doesn't take very long).
As the turkey is finished, place on serving platter.
Mix in bell pepper-onion-garlic mixture as it is finished.
Serve with tortillas and whatever else makes you happy!

title: company's coming casserole
directions: Brown meat; add vegetables.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add cooked noodles.
Put mixture into shallow baking dishes.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Top with cheese and cook until cheese is melted.
Serves 20.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients; mix.
Add pineapple last. Drop by teaspoons. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: hawaiian cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Frost cookies and decorate with coconut and cherry halves.

title: barbie's casserole
directions: Saute the onion and celery in oil.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to a large casserole dish.
Top with 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle 1 stick margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: margaret's brownies
directions: Cream together the butter and the sugar.
Beat the eggs until they are light, add the vanilla and eggs to butter and sugar, mixing well.
Add the cocoa and nuts; mix again.
Pour in greased and floured pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: deluxe spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach (according to package directions).
Drain and squeeze dry.
Mix together all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours. Roll into balls.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
When frozen, store in plastic bags until needed.
Thaw before baking.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes (don't overbake).

title: steve's no-fat pasta (almost)
directions: Saute chopped garlic and onions in olive oil until soft.
Have large pot of water boiling for pasta.
Add drained capers, chopped tomatoes, chopped artichokes, chicken broth, salt and pepper. Simmer approximately 25 to 30 minutes on low heat.
Cook pasta last 10 minutes while mixture is simmering.
Drain pasta; put it and tomato mixture back into large pot.
Mix well.
Sprinkle portions with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8 easily.

title: tex-mix dip
directions: 1st Layer:
2 cans Frito bean dip.

title: seafood creole
directions: Cook and stir onion in margarine (or butter) in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes.
Stir in seafood; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Slice chicken breasts into bite size strips and brown in large skillet with oil.
Add Taco Bell taco seasoning mix and water; simmer until reduced.
Clean and slice all remaining vegetables for the salad.
Combine all dressing ingredients and blend well.
Pour into serving dish.
Place the salad into serving bowl and top with warm chicken.
Serve with Taco Bell tortilla chips and Avocado Picante Dressing.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Takes 20 minutes.

title: every day meat loaf
directions: Form loaf in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes with or without tomato sauce.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients except marshmallows.
Pour in casserole dish after greasing.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with marshmallows.
Brown in broiler.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Mix cheese and shortening with hands.
Add yolks and continue working until well blended.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use dough, sprinkle powdered sugar on board and roll out.
Cut in squares and fill.
We use walnuts, apricots or lekvar.
Bake in a quick oven (350°) for about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well. Add other ingredients and beat until well blended.
Chill dough several hours.
Shape dough into small balls and roll in sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: stewp
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in a large pot. Drain. Add potatoes, onion, carrots and Worcestershire sauce. Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat until potatoes and carrots are done. Great with fried cornbread.

title: chicken dish
directions: Saut onion in stick of butter. Mix with herb stuffing and 2 cups chicken broth. Then for bottom layer, put 1 can of chicken soup, mixed with 3/4 cup milk. For middle layer, put in cut up chicken. For top layer, put the Pepperidge Farm stuffing mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until it bubbles.

title: mchugh irish stew
directions: Place everything in crock-pot; salt and pepper.
Cook on low 8 to 9 hours or 5 to 6 hours on high.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook spaghetti; toss all with 2 forks, except a small amount of cheese for topping.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Beat margarine and peanut butter on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup flour, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Stir in remaining flour.
Press dough evenly into a 12 or 14-inch pizza pan, forming a rim around the edge.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes more or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Cool; cut into wedges. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Beat margarine, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir together baking powder and flour.
Combine milk and flavorings.
Alternate flour and milk mixtures into dough, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 to 15 minutes until tender (don't cover).
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Stir all together.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs and cheese.
Add the zucchini mix to this and mix well.
Press crescent rolls into an 8-inch deep pie dish.
Pour zucchini mixture over crescent roll crust.
Press evenly.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or if using a glass pie dish, reduce temperature to 350°.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a serving platter as the first layer. Combine sour cream and taco seasoning, this will be the second layer. Continue layering ingredients in the order given. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: louisiana praline yams
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor. Cover and process until smooth.
Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix and form into balls. Arrange in shallow baking pan (bottom of broiler pan).

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix and heat in double boiler until melted.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
Makes 1 quart.
Serve with corn chips or Bugles.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 2 to 5 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Mix dressing just before ready to serve.
Mix ingredients and dressings and serve.

title: peanut cereal candy
directions: Mix sugar and Karo together in small saucepan. Cook until it comes to a full boil. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla flavoring. Add corn flakes to mixture. Spread into small buttered pan.

title: cooked chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Put the sugar, syrup, milk and chocolate in large sauce pan. Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook until a small amount of mixture forms a very soft ball in very cold water (232 degrees on candy thermometer) stirring occasionally to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and add butter without stirring and cook until lukewarm about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until frosting is creamy.
Spread quickly over cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken, carrots and potatoes into bite size pieces.
Cook until done.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, put chicken mixture. Mix together garden peas, buttermilk, margarine and flour.
Pour this over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° about 30 minutes.

title: banana berry brownie pizza(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil.
Mix together brownie mix, water, oil and egg in large bowl until well blended. Pour into greased and floured 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: connie's mini quiche
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with margarine and flour.
Roll into a ball and divide into 24 small balls for very small muffin tins and 18 for small 2-inch tins.
Place each ball in tin and flatten to shape.
In each cup put layer of onion, meat filler and cheese.
At this point, they may be refrigerated or frozen. Just before serving, fill each cup with mixture of egg and milk beaten together. Sprinkle
top with paprika.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes, then bake at 350°
for 10 minutes more or until top is brown.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour with salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans, one large pan or 4 small.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or with whipped cream.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix chopped artichokes with cheese and mayonnaise in a 2-quart glass dish.
Microwave on High 5 to 8 minutes, stirring once, until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: custard pie
directions: Make pastry for one crust pie.
Mix all ingredients, except milk, in a bowl and whisk.
Slowly pour in scalded milk and mix. Pour into pie shell and bake at 425 for 25-30 minutes.

title: vegetable diet soup
directions: Cut vegetables in small pieces.
Boil, covered, for 10 minutes.
Lower heat and cook until vegetables are soft.
You can use this soup when dieting.
Eat all the soup you want.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Bring to a boil the first 7 ingredients.
Blend together the remaining ingredients.
Put all of the ingredients together and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tea cake recipe
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Work rest of ingredients in gradually.
Roll into small balls (if needed, add more flour to make "rolling" dough).
Dip glass in a sugar and cinnamon mixture; mash cookies flat.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 300° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
75 tea cakes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender Blend flour, chili powder and salt into the vegetable mixture.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp to the vegetable mixture.
Heat thoroughly. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Form into balls, dip in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients except hominy and cracker crumbs.
When mixture is thickened, add hominy.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart buttered bowl.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in the shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Take out and knead enough to hold together.
Roll dough into 1/2-inch thickness and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in pan.
Let rise for approximately 4 hours at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans and onion slices.
Combine the other ingredients and pour over the bean mixture.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: poor man's charlotte russe
directions: Place strawberries into a baking dish.
Cover strawberries with sour cream.
Cover this mixture thoroughly with brown sugar.
Place into preheated oven at 350° and bake until bubbling (20 to 25 minutes).
Serve in dessert glasses, hot or cold.

title: donut muffin
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add with milk to egg mixture.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan at once and roll in melted butter, then in remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fix rice according to directions on box.
Add tomatoes, brown pork chops and tear apart.
Add to rice.
When finished, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: one pan blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in 11 x 7-inch baking pan. Add milk, Bisquick mix and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Drop spoonfuls of pie filling over batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until deep golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip. Yield: 8 servings

title: chocolate raisin chewies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa powder, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture at low speed until just blended.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes, or until cookies are set.
Do not overbake.
Cookies should be soft and moist.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to kitchen counter.

title: low-fat oat bran muffins
directions: Pour water over raisins or dates.
Sift sugar, flour, oat bran and soda.
Combine honey, if used, egg whites, oil and milk and blend well.
Combine with water and raisins.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and pour wet ingredients in the well. Mix only enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Batter can be kept in fridge up to six weeks.

title: zucchini round pancakes
directions: Mix all together and fry in oil.

title: pickles
directions: Drain cucumbers; cut into slices.
Place 1/2 in jar and pour 2 1/2 pounds sugar over.
Add 1 teaspoon pickling spice, 1/2 teaspoon
mustard
seed and 1 garlic button.
Add rest of cucumbers
and repeat.
Let stand 5 days.
After 3rd day, stir with wooden spoon (use nothing metal).

title: pasta con amora
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients.
Add the 2 cheeses.
Serve immediately over cooked ziti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and flour gradually.
Cream until fluffy.
Add syrup; beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add broken pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: italian rice
directions: Use enough salad oil to cover bottom of heavy skillet.
Pour in raw rice and heat on medium-high heat until rice starts to fry and turns white.
Add mushrooms and juice and turn to low heat.
Cover and cook until liquid is gone, about 20 minutes.
Add onion soup, Italian seasonings, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Cover; cook until liquid gone and rice is tender, stirring once or twice. Serves 6.

title: pearadice bread
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine pears, syrup, cheese, nuts and oil.
Mix liquid and dry ingredients until moistened.
Turn batter into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then cool on wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: iris' puppy chow
directions: In large plastic bowl, put Crispix and gently pour other ingredients over, mixing with a wooden spoon.
Sift 2 cups powdered sugar over cereal and stir to coat.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes. Fry bacon; remove bacon and drain on paper towel. Remove frying pan from heat and slice 1/2 onion into grease. Put back on heat; stir in sugar and flour. When beginning to thicken, add vinegar and water. Cook until thickened. Pour over and mix into potatoes which have been salted and peppered to taste and 1/2 onion sliced in.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Flour and fry pork chops in oil.
Set aside.
Spread rice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1 tablespoon soup mix and sprinkle the rest evenly over the rice.
Drain mushrooms and put over rice. Keep the liquid.
Put pimentos over rice.
Add enough water to mushroom and pimento liquid to make 2 3/4 cups.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Pour liquid over meat and rice.
Dot with butter.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mussels in cilantro & serrano cream
directions: In a large saute pan, heat the olive oil and butter.
Add the shallots, mussels, garlic and wine.
Cover and allow to cook over medium heat for 3 minutes or until mussels have opened.
Uncover and remove mussels.
Discard any mussels that have not opened, cover the rest and set them aside.

Reduce the remaining liquid by half and then add the cream tomato, onions, cilantro and chilis. Place opened mussels back in pan. Continue cooking 2 more minutes. Remove mussels and arrange them on a serving plate.
Continue cooking sauce until it reaches desired consistency.
Pour over mussels and serve immediately.

title: al kelley's s.o.s
directions: Cook beef in frypan; drain off excess fat and set aside.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend 3 tablespoons flour and milk until smooth; blend with the melted margarine.
Add 6 or 7 ounces cheese, in strips, to milk sauce over low heat until smooth.
Add more cheese or milk to control sauce consistency.
Add cooked beef to cheese sauce and mix well.
Serve over toast.
Can add pepper, onion powder or garlic powder to taste.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Add flour; mix well. Get all lumps out.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Makes own crust.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked apples(in the microwave)
directions: Core (without cutting through the bottom of apples) and peel upper half of apples.
Place an inch apart in a glass or ceramic baking dish.
Fill centers with a mixture of sugar, spices and nuts.
Pour 1/2 teaspoon juice in each.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and microwave on High 7 to 10 minutes, rotating dish 180° after 4 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with Manwich or ketchup before baking, if desired.
Serve with peas, corn or mashed potatoes.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook until thick and clear.
Take from fire.
Add red food coloring and 1/2 package strawberry Jell-O.
Stir well.
Let cool.
Wash strawberries while cooling glaze.
Top with strawberries.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain and rinse peas.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: tea ade
directions: Makes a great hot weather drink!!

title: banana flip
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham crackers and combine.
Spread over bottom of pan.
Mix 2 sticks margarine (softened), sugar and eggs; beat for no less than 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over crust.
Slice bananas; place over the mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Top with whipped cream, cherries and nuts.

title: radicchio with bacon
directions: Heat the oil in a skillet over low heat.
Add the pancetta and onion; saute for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, green chilies and onion together and drain. Add beans and tomatoes.
Mix taco seasoning, dressing mix and water together.
Add to soup mixture.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with grated cheese and Doritos.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Combine the next 3 ingredients. Combine all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Bake at 350°.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
When it is mixed, shape into small logs.
Wrap in foil.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Slice as needed.

title: chili sauce(canned)
directions: Scald, peel and cut up tomatoes.
Chop onions and peppers. Place all ingredients in a kettle; simmer for approximately 2 hours, stirring constantly.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix 1st three ingredients; add milk.
Sift other dry ingredients together and add, mixing well.
Roll dough on floured board and cut out doughnuts, about 1/2-inch thick.
Carefully place in hot fat that is 380°.
Brown each side and drain on paper towels.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well. Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Top with favorite topping.

title: cheese balls
directions: Set all cheeses out until softened and grate all together. Mix 15 minutes with hands.
Roll into 2 balls, then roll in crushed pecans and chopped parsley.
Refrigerate.
Make a few days in advance and thaw 1 hour before eating.
Eat on Town House or Ritz crackers.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar added and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix in 2 cups flour, potatoes and shortening.
Add eggs and remaining sugar.
Add remaining 4 cups flour and salt; mix well.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours until doubled. Slightly knead dough on floured surface and roll out 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 2 inch circles and place on buttered baking sheets, brushing tops with melted butter.
Let rise 1 hour and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: In saucepan, blend milk into flour, stir constantly over medium heat until mixture is like thick paste.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Blend together shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, egg, soda, salt and vanilla until light.
Mix in 2 cups flour.
Press 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with mixture of chocolate sauce, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Add oatmeal to remaining dough.
Crumble over filling. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: In saucepan, combine chocolate and milk. Stir over low heat until chocolate melts. Remove from heat and stir in sugar and nuts. Chill a few minutes, then form into 1-inch balls. Roll in coconut. Makes 30 balls.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Prepare cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let this stand 2 hours. Squeeze all liquid off mixture.
Place sugar and vinegar in pan and boil only until sugar is dissolved; set aside to cool.
When cool, pack layer of cucumbers and onions in container, then a little of your liquid and celery seed.
Continue layering until container is 1-inch from top.
Freeze.

title: chocolate chip treasure cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix graham crackers, flour and baking powder.
In large bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk and butter until smooth.
Add crumb mixture and mix well. Stir in coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Store loosely covered at room temperature. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In large skillet, add meat and garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until sauce has thickened; stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf. Serve over hot spaghetti.
Pass Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: english muffins crabbies
directions: Mix altogether; spread on English muffins.
Put under broiler for about 5 minutes.
Check at 2 minutes.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks, honey, milk and melted butter or safflower oil.
Sift whole wheat pastry flour, buckwheat flour, sea salt and baking powder together.
Stir egg yolk mixture into flour mixture. Beat egg whites until they form stiff shiny peaks.
Gently fold into batter.

title: florentine dip
directions: Combine the cheese, yogurt and milk, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: whipped potatoes with olive oil and parmesan
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain.
Peel potatoes and transfer to large bowl.
Add 3/4 cup of broth.
Using electric mixer, beat potato mixture until smooth.
Gradually beat in oil and then 3/4 cup cheese, adding more broth if very thick.
Stir in chives.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with additional grated cheese.
Great with grilled meat.

title: mildred hunt's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, 2 minutes apart.
Alternate flour and milk; add flavoring and coconut.
Line tube pan or spray Pam on nonstick loaf pans. Makes 1 large and 1 small loaf.
Put in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: santa claus cakes
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and sugar together.
Mix well with dates and nuts.
Mix eggs with dry ingredients.
Spread about 1/2-inch thick on a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes.
Cut, while warm, into small bars and roll in granulated sugar.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Roll small balls of sugar cookie dough to fill mini muffin pans not quite half full.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Immediately push peanut butter cup into center of each muffin and flash freeze for about 10 minutes.
Insert a sharp knife into pan to pop them out.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple cranberry squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in undrained pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine (or cranberry juice).
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Fold in pecans and turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan (for thinner, but larger squares, use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan).
Chill until firm.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Put in roaster or baking dish.
Cook at 250° for 5 to 6 hours. During last hour, add 1 (4 ounce) can mushrooms and potatoes. Delicious with crusty bread and salad.

title: freezer apples for apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until just tender.
Can be frozen in bags or in large plastic covered containers.
Scoop out desired amount to make pie using your favorite recipe.

title: congealed pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook to thicken.
Spread in an oblong glass dish.
Top with whipped cream and grated cheese.

title: cheesy oven potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in wedges.
Leave skin on if desired.
Combine next four ingredients.
Dip potatoes in melted margarine and sprinkle with cheese mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes in a shallow roasting pan.
Stir occasionally while baking.

title: "dump-together" soup
directions: Brown meat in a 4 to 6-quart pan.
Add as much water as you desire.
Add remaining ingredients, except for vegetables.
One hour before serving, add vegetables.
May be cooked all day or for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious with hot corn bread.

title: iced spice tea
directions: Boil sugar and 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Add hot water and tea bags.
Steep 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Serve over ice.
Garnish.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fresh broccoli pasta
directions: Melt butter and oil.
Brown garlic, put in tomatoes and chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Cook pasta.
Put broccoli in sauce for last 10 minutes of cooking (this can be increased in cooking time depending upon how crunchy you like your vegetables).
When pasta is done, mix sauce with pasta and serve.

title: oriental soup
directions: Heat broth; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes until ingredients are hot.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Arrange pork chops in pan.
Salt and pepper each chop and place an onion slice and lemon slice on each one.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pour about a tablespoon of catsup on each chop. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: jello salad mold
directions: Add sandwich spread, chicken broth and salt and pepper.
Add more pickles if you want to.
You can add eggs or anything else you want.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese in a bowl.
Add sugar gradually beating.
Add eggs and beat well.
Beat in lemon juice, vanilla, cornstarch and flour. Add melted butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour into a 9-inch or 10-inch spring-form pan (greased).
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Don't peek.
Turn off heat and leave cake in oven for 2 hours longer.
Cool 2 hours at room temperature, then refrigerate.

title: vanilla milk chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually add flour mixture until combined. Stir in chips, rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
These cookies are chewy with a touch of spice.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, and milk. Add the bread crumbs, onion, and salt. Crumple beef over mixture and mix well. Shape into 1 inch balls.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until very crisp; drain and crumble.
Now add beans, bacon, onion, mustard, brown sugar and pineapple (drained).
Cook over low heat on top of stove or may be baked in oven for about 45 minutes to an hour.
Very good with hamburgers and a salad.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off grease.
Place in a casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion flakes in a pan.
Drain off fat. Add tomato juice, water, stewed tomatoes and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil.
Add bag of frozen vegetables, potatoes and celery.
Cook until vegetables are done, about 45 to 60 minutes. During the last 15 minutes, add spaghetti.
It is ready to serve when vegetables and spaghetti are done.

title: beef noodle marzetti
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown meat.
Pour off fat. Add green peppers, onions and garlic.
Cook and stir until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked noodles.
Turn into greased 3-quart shallow baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Cover.
Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with cheese.
Bake 3 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Beat cream cheese until softened; blend in confectioners sugar.
Add peanut butter and beat.
Fold 3/4 of the whipped topping into the above mixture. pour into pie shell.
Swirl chocolate syrup over top and cover with remaining whipped topping.
This can be served soon after it is made or it can be frozen.

title: no-egg apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into muffin pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° in regular oven or at 450° in toaster oven.

title: home made salad dressing
directions: Mix together 2 - 8 oz. containers Cool Whip and 2 small pkg. vanilla instant pudding mixes.
Then Add 1 package of crushed Keebler cookies, 2 small cans of mandarin oranges, drained.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Leave out 1/2 cup flour to dredge fruit and nuts in.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, which has been sifted with spices and soda.
Add milk, whiskey and vanilla. Mix until well blended.
Pour over fruit and nut mixture.
Mix well.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoon on well-greased cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chops - sweet and sour
directions: Mix the ginger, salt, pepper, paprika and flour together. Coat both sides of the chops in this mixture.
In skillet, heat shortening and chops and cook over low heat until brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: layered salad
directions: Start with a large bowl.
Begin layering with the lettuce. Next you layer with your vegetables; they should be in bite size pieces; set aside.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Mix pineapple (undrained) with creamed mixture. Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom steaks
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Spoon mixture into a pan which has heated oil in it and form into patties.
Brown.
Put into casserole and cover with mixture of mushroom soup, water and broth.
Place in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream caramel filling for cake
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine.
Mix flour and sugar together and stir into butter. Add cream.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Cool and spread over cake.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot and pineapple cake
directions: Chop and blend dates, pecans and raisins.
Add water and boil 3 minutes.
Add corn oil margarine; stir and cool.
In mixing bowl, blend date mixture with flour, soda, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add pineapple, carrots and coconut; mix.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in well to blend.
Cut in shortening until mixture is fine.
Stir in oats.
Add egg and milk, stirring just until ingredients are moistened.
Fill paper lined muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: conch chowder
directions: In small amount of olive oil, saute garlic until soft but not brown; remove.
Combine pepperoni, onions, peppers, tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil, parsley, salt and pepper and water. Simmer 1 hour.
Use food processor to break up tissue and chop conch into small pieces.
Add conch, shrimp, potatoes, okra and cook another hour, or until done.
Do not overcook.

title: date rolls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients slowly until thick.
Add sugar and take off stove.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
When cool enough to handle, roll in Angel Flake coconut.

title: chicken and spinach enchiladas(mexican meal)
directions: Boil chicken 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken and let cool slightly. Bone chicken, dice and set aside.
Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well. Reserve 1 cup spinach broth. Set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in spinach and chicken. Set aside.
Combine soup, reserved spinach broth, milk, green chiles, sour cream and half of the cheese in a bowl.
Mix well. Stir half of the sauce mixture into chicken mixture.
Reserve remaining sauce.
Spoon chicken mixture evenly down center of each tortilla.
Roll up tortillas and place, seam down, into 2 lightly greased pans. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 16; you may halve the recipe, if you want.

title: banana-pineapple cake(no eggs)
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla, bananas, pineapple, nuts and salad oil.
Mix well.
Do not beat.
Pour mixture into a floured and greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Cut apples up.
Put in pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar with the flour. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Place sliced onion over ground beef.
Place sliced potatoes over onions.
Place cheese over potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup over cheese.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: picadillo de pollo mexico
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with nonstick spray and warm the pan over medium high heat for 1 minute.
Add the chicken, onions and garlic and cook, stirring frequently, until the chicken is lightly brown and is cooked through.
Stir in the tomato, raisins, olives, peppers, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring the mixture to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until most liquid has evaporated, about 5 minutes.
Spoon down the center of each warm tortilla. Roll up the tortilla and serve.
Serves 4.

title: rice casserole
directions: Simmer rice and water with lid on for 20 minutes.
Add Accent, green chilies and sour cream, cover with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Put into greased dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Season with poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Let cool, then debone.
Melt shortening in boiling water.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add water mixture slowly to make soft dough.
Place, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out thin.
Cut in squares.
Add to liquid and chicken 1 cup milk and bring to boil.
Add dumplings.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered.
Stir with knife.
Simmer 20 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: the easy way to bake a blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour the juice into a container.
In small saucepan, combine blackberries and add sugar to your taste.
Pour berries over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top and bake for 10 minutes.

title: creme caramel(vanilla custard with caramel sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 340° (170°C).
Split the vanilla bean in two lengthwise and place in a saucepan with the milk.
Bring to simmer, then remove from heat.
Cover and let stand to infuse.
Place half the sugar in a saucepan.
Add the lemon juice and water and bring to boil.
Cook until an amber colored caramel forms.
Remove from heat and pour the caramel into a 2-quart metal charlotte mold, souffle dish or cake tin; it may also be divided into individual souffle dishes.
Quickly turn the mold in your hands so the caramel coats the bottom and sides.
Break the eggs into a large bowl and add the remaining sugar.
Whisk until well blended, then pour delicately the hot milk on this mixture.
Put the mixture into the mold through a fine sieve.
Place the mold in a water bath and bake for 1 hour (45 minutes for individual molds) or until the custard is set and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove the Creme Caramel from the water bath and let cool.
Unmold onto a plate and serve at room temperature or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: uncooked pepper relish
directions: Mix; let stand overnight. Pack cold in warm jars and seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients.
Combine with milk mixture.
Mix well. Pour into well buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, add oil.
Cook carrots, celery and onions until lightly browned.
Remove vegetables with slotted spoon.
Place chicken, bay leaf, bouillon, salt and 6 cups water in Dutch oven.
Boil until chicken is done.
When chicken is done, remove and debone.
Add vegetables and rice to broth and heat until rice is done.
Add chicken (in bite size pieces) and bring to a boil.
Discard bay leaf and serve.

title: lemon cole slaw
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Combine seasonings in a saucepan.
Add oil and vinegar; heat to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the jello.
Continue to stir until jello is dissolved. Cool, then pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Will keep for days in the refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix well brown sugar, butter or margarine, egg and vanilla and add 1 small can drained, crushed pineapple.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and walnuts.
Add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: london broil
directions: Grill:
Use a piece of beef according to your family size. Lay in 2 pieces of heavy foil.
Pour bottle of Italian dressing over beef.
Sprinkle top only with garlic salt according to taste. Cover tightly with tinfoil.
Check every 15 minutes until tender. Be careful not to poke holes in your foil, as the juices will disappear.

title: shortcut stroganoff
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add beef, celery and onion and cook until browned and juices evaporate, stirring often.
Drain; put back in skillet.
Add soup, water and pasta.
Heat to a boil.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes or until done, stirring.
Heat through. Serves 4.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread into pie plate and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Serve hot with crackers or toast rounds.

title: honey apple rings
directions: Saute in wine, chicken broth, vermouth or flavored vinegar. Always use a nonstick pan to cook in and use a nonfat cooking spray.
Never use butter, lard, shortening or hydrogenated vegetable oil to cook with.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Prepare egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain. In medium size saucepan, melt butter.
Cook celery and onion until tender. Add soup, milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Combine noodles, cheese sauce, carrots, mushrooms, chicken, salt and pepper.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 6 servings.

title: turtle pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese in a bowl. Mix coconut, nuts and butter in a skillet. Cook until golden brown.
Put half of Cool Whip mixture in bottom of each pie shell, then put coconut mixture and drizzle caramel syrup, then make another layer of Cool Whip, then coconut and syrup.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas morning wife saver
directions: In 9 x 13-inch buttered glass baking dish, put in 8 slices of bread.
Add pieces to cover dish entirely.
Cover bread with slices of Canadian bacon or ham, sliced thin.
Lay slices of Cheddar cheese on top and then cover with slices of bread to make it like a sandwich.
In a bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper, then add dry mustard, onion, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce, milk and Tabasco.
Pour over the sandwiches.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, melt butter and pour over top.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: wacky cake
directions: Measure into sifter the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt; sift dry ingredients right into 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan. Make 3 holes in dry mixture.
Place oil, vinegar and vanilla equally into holes.
Pour over all 1 cup water.
Stir with fork until blended.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: tomato-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Toss with a wooden spoon.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top with: 1/2 c. melted margarine mixed with finely crushed cornflakes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Layer ingredients in order given and top with Bisquick and milk, mixed together.
Pour melted butter over all.
Make sure no vegetables are showing.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for an hour or until chicken is tender, basting frequently.
Serve with hot rice.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter a Bundt pan.
Place dinner rolls in pan, forming a circle.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding mix over rolls. Top with nuts.
Blend butter, brown sugar and cinnamon in saucepan. Bring to a boil and pour over buns.
Let set at room temperature overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix with mixer. Spread on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer with onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Pour on bottle of taco sauce.
Top with cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut up broccoli.
Mix with all ingredients except bacon.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Before serving, stir in bacon or spread bacon on top.

title: chicken with toasted almonds
directions: Slice chicken breasts into long thin slivers.
To make them easier to slice, store in freezer until partially frozen.
Then let thaw at room temperature.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into deep baking dish.
Stir together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over margarine.
Pour sliced peaches or pie filling over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.
(The flour will rise to the top and form a crust.)

title: caldeirada(fisherman stew)
directions: Scrub the clams/mussels under running water.
Set aside. Saute the onion, pepper and garlic for 5 minutes in 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
Add tomatoes and their liquid and bring to a boil. Cut the fish into 1 1/2-inch wide pieces.
If using squid, clean thoroughly and cut into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Place the clams/mussels in the bottom of a heavy kettle.
Pour 4 tablespoons olive oil in kettle.
Scatter 1/2 the vegetable mixture over the shellfish.
Add fish and squid; spread the rest of the vegetable mixture over the top.
Pour on the wine.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until clams are open and fish flakes easily, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: v-8 congealed salad
directions: Mix and chill lemon jello, V-8 juice, salt and onion.
Mix cottage cheese, mayonnaise, celery, olives and bell pepper; add to jello mixture and mix all together.
Chill.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Combine crabmeat and shrimp; add celery, green pepper, onion and pimiento.
Blend in separate bowl, sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir into seafood mixture.
Spoon into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over seafood mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage and squash casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: brunch scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease cookie sheet. Sift flour and baking powder into medium bowl. Cut margarine into flour to form a fine crumble. Make a well in center; add milk and raisins. Knead gently together, being careful not to overmix. Dough will be sticky. On a generously floured surface, roll out dough to 3/4 inch thickness. Using a pastry cutter, cut out scones. Transfer to prepared pan; brush tops with egg yolk. Allow to stand 15 minutes. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until risen and lightly golden brown on top. Do not over bake or they will be dry. Remove to a rack to cool.

title: maryann's pork tenderloin
directions: Note:
Marinate 24 hours.
Tenderloins come 2 to a package. This recipe is enough for 2 packages.

title: sausage and bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain; add other ingredients and simmer until beans are tender.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Layer Oreo cookies into dish.
Place a layer of chocolate pudding and then a layer of Cool Whip.
Continue the layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pan-fried venison chops
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Get it hot enough to almost smoke.
Crush garlic cloves and rub a little into one side of chop. Salt and pepper same side.
Place in skillet, seasoned side down. Now season the "up" side while the first side browns.
Venison is tough and dry if overdone, so serve chops medium rare.
When blood oozes to the surface of the meat, it's time to turn.
Wait for blood to surface again, then they're ready.
Serve hot from skillet with rice or potatoes and broccoli or other green vegetable.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan, stirring until crumbly.
Add onion and spices, mixing well.
Stir in flour and tomatoes with 5 cups water.
Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring oleo, cocoa and coffee to boil.
Mix hot ingredients with dry mixture in bowl.
Bake in cookie sheet with sides greased or sprayed with Pam at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with your favorite chocolate frosting or:

title: tasty pea salad
directions: Thaw peas about 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss with sour cream.

title: pea salad
directions: Place lettuce in a 9 x 13 pan.
Layer onions, peas and celery. Spread mayonnaise over all.
Sprinkle sugar.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: date balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg and dates in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly for 10 minutes.
Cool.
In a bowl mix Rice Krispies and nuts; pour into date mixture.
Use hands to mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar or coconut.

title: apple tart
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts to liquid mixture.
Mix well and bake in a well-greased 8 x 12 x 4-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with ice cream.

title: banana coconut cream spread
directions: In medium bowl,
combine cream cheese, honey and orange juice. Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in banana and coconut.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: *May use mixture of both.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer in this order:
lettuce, carrots, bell pepper, onion and peas.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add 1-inch layer of mayonnaise, cheese and bacon bits.
Seal and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: black russian brownies
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350F.

Line bottom of a 13 x 9 inch pan with wax paper. Melt chocolate and butter with pepper in a sauce pan over low heat. Remove from heat. combine eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl, beat well. Stir in cooled chocolate mixture, Kahlua and Vodka. Combine flour, salt and baking powder, add chocolate mixture and stir. Add walnuts. Spread in pan. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool on wire rack, cut into bars. Sprinkle with powdered sugar if you like.

title: minnesota wild rice soup
directions: Wash rice well and drain.
Cook rice in chicken broth and water for approximately 45 minutes.
While rice is cooking, saute vegetables in margarine until transparent.
Add flour and stir until thickened.
Add rice and chicken stock to vegetables, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings, ham, almonds and cream or milk.
Heat.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion in a skillet. Brown and drain. Cook noodles by directions and drain. While noodles are cooking, in a large pan, combine spaghetti mix, tomatoes, paste, sauce, water, butter, salt, pepper, and meat. Simmer for 20 minutes. In a large oven dish, layer noodles on the bottom, then sauce mixture, mozerella cheese, cottage cheese, and parmesan cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 375 for 25-30 minutes until bubbly and hot in the middle.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in pineapple juice.
Add orange juice (thawed), sugar and water.
Stir well.
Add ginger ale and ice when ready to serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter on high speed of mixer. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add flour and beat until smooth. Add eggs and beat until well blended. Add buttermilk and vanilla; beat well. Pour into pie shell and bake 5 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set. Cool to room temperature; chill.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut cake in small pieces.
Prepare mousse according to directions.
Layer half the cake in a truffle or glass bowl, pressing the cake to the bottom of the pan.
Top with half the mousse, then half the Cool Whip. Chop the candy and sprinkle half the candy bars over the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and refrigerate.

title: joe bailey cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar to which cocoa has been well mixed. Add in order:
well beaten egg yolks, coffee, flour and buttermilk in which soda has been dissolved, vanilla and well-beaten egg whites.
Bake in two 9-inch layers in moderate 350° oven for 40 minutes, until done.

title: icicle cucumber pickle
directions: Mix water and salt. Pour over cucumbers and let stand one week. Stir after third day to keep down scum.
Drain and add alum about the size of a walnut. Powdered will do.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours or no more than 2 days.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: mexican chimichangas
directions: Mix all ingredients (add flour, if too thin).
On regular flour tortilla (warm slightly in microwave oven so easy to fold), put one serving (spoon size) of chicken mixture.
Fold bottom of tortilla up, then both sides in, then turn it all up and over. Fry in hot oil, flaps sides down (to keep mixture in).
Fry on both sides until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Spoon mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: spareribs
directions: Select meaty spareribs.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in roaster and cover with onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake in moderate (350°) oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally, turning ribs once or twice.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes to brown ribs.
Serves 6.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a large frypan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, green pepper and garlic; saute about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Slowly add 1 1/2 cups of warm chicken broth and the warm cream, stirring until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and add wine.
To the beaten egg yolks, add several tablespoons of the hot white sauce, stirring well, then add mixture to frying pan; continue to stir.
Add chicken pieces, stirring until
mixture is thoroughly heated, about 3 or 4 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Spray the skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add broccoli, chopped peppers, zucchini, squash and garlic to skillet.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and peas and saute for 2 minutes more.
Place parsley, basil leaves and chicken bouillon in food processor fitted with the metal blade and process until parsley is finely chopped.
Cook pasta according to package directions and drain.
Add parsley mixture and vegetables and toss well.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in saucepan over low heat.
Slice hot dogs into bite-size pieces.
Add to sauce and heat through.
Serve hot.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water.
Let cool.
Soften cream cheese with a little milk.
Use beater; beat the cream cheese, Cool Whip and Jell-O together.
Add marshmallows.
Line bottom of glass dish with drained fruit.
Pour Jell-O mixture over fruit.
Refrigerate until set.

title: deluxe cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl with mixer at low speed, beat cheese with eggs, sugar and vanilla just until mixed.
Beat at high speed until smooth; pour into crust.
Bake 35 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and add cherry pie filling (or other favorite fruit filling) and chill 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: You also need a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: meatballs
directions: After stirring the ingredients, add 2 pounds of ground chuck. Shape into meatballs about 2 inches in diameter.
Coat a shallow roasting pan with non-stick cooking spray.
Space the meatballs in the pan so they don't touch.
Cover bottom of pan with 1 cup low-sodium beef broth.
Bake at 450 degrees for 25 minutes or until they are cooked through.
Can use with your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Pan drippings may be used in the sauce.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Brown cut up fryers in 1 tablespoon oil. Drain and blot dry. Add onions, vermouth, parsley, garlic clove, tarragon, salt, pepper and water. Cover. Simmer on top of stove or bake, covered, in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes. Stir lemon juice into sauce and simmer, uncovered, until reduced to sauce consistency. Garnish top of each piece of chicken with thin slices of lemon. Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rich cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour and salt.
Add gradually; stir until smooth.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with walnut half.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: gobbler cookies
directions: Add milk gradually to peanut butter in medium bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whip until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 8 of the cookies.
Top with remaining cookies, pressing lightly.

title: holly day cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter together in double boiler.
Add food coloring, vanilla and Frosted Flakes.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Drop 3 or 4 red hots on top of each cookie.

title: southern cream cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix well.
Sift together, then add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Then add walnuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Grease bottom of glass; dip into mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Press cookie flat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chess cake(easy and delicious!)
directions: Beat 1 egg and butter into cake mix. Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan. (Mixture will be crumbly.)
Beat remaining ingredients together and spread over first layer. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top will be golden brown in spots and just firm.
Cool and cut.

title: church cake
directions: Grease sides and bottom of angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with half of the chopped nuts and chocolate sprinkles mixture.
Mix the batter together and pour half of batter on top of nuts and sprinkles.
Add the rest of nuts and sprinkles.
Cover with the remaining batter.
Cut through gently with a knife to slightly mix the chocolate sprinkles and nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test for doneness with cake tester. Do not turn pan upside down to cool.
Cake will fall out.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix well ingredients and fill greased muffin cups half full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon crumb bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat cake mix, butter and 1 egg in large bowl until crumbly. Stir in saltine crumbs. Set aside 2 cups crumb mixture. Press remaining mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly golden. With mixer or wire whisk, beat egg yolks. Add Eagle brand and then add ReaLemon. Spread over pressed crumb mixture. Top with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 25 minutes longer or until set and top is golden. Cool. Refrigerate 2 hours. Cut into bars and serve. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator. Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: easy taco dinner
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until meat is light brown.
Drain.

title: tangerine and chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces, then place them in a medium bowl along with tangerines, pecans, raisins and scallions.
In a small bowl, stir in oil, juice and rosemary.
Pour over salad and toss well or until all pieces are lightly coated.
Serve at room temperature as a main dish salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccolli salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients and chill for 3 hours. Add remaining ingredients. And serve chilled.

title: potato gratin with mustard and gruyere cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Overlap 1/3 of potatoes in dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon dill weed and 1/3 of cheese. Repeat everything.
Whisk cream, broth and mustard in bowl.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake until tender and top is crusty and brown, about 1/2 hour.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Cook chicken in salt and water until tender.
Dice chicken and set aside.
Strain broth, and add vegetables; cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup, milk, salt, pepper, parsley, and butter to vegetables.
Mix well then add cheese.
Reduce to low heat, and cook until creamy.
Garnish with more cheese before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, syrup, peanuts and salt for 8 minutes on High.
Stir once.
Stir in butter and cook 2 more minutes on High. Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Break into pieces when cold.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple on bottom of casserole dish. Mix flour, cheese and sugar. Sprinkle over pineapple. Mix crackers and butter and spread evenly over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli on paper towel. Boil chicken and cut it up in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, soup, water and Miracle Whip and add it to the broccoli and chicken (also seasoning from stuffing).
Pour dry Stove Top over all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Put onions on and bake 10 more minutes. (Onion rings can also be optional.
Almonds go in with liquids but are optional.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add syrup, vanilla and nuts. Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 minutes, or until firm.

title: hidden valley spinach dip
directions: Mix party dip with sour cream.
Add drained and chopped spinach and water chestnuts.
Blend together well and serve with pieces of rye bread or crackers.

title: combination baked beans
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Drain bacon on paper towels.
Cook onion in drippings, stirring constantly, until tender; drain.
Combine onion, bacon, vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 2 lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dishes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Yields 18 servings.

title: spanish pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Gradually add white vinegar and vanilla. Beat until shiny.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and leave in oven overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly sour cream and mushroom soup.
Then add cubed chicken and mix well.
Spread this over the bottom of 9 x 13-inch shallow baking pan or dish.
Melt oleo and chicken broth together until hot.
Put the stuffing mix in a bowl large enough for mixing.
Pour the chicken broth mixture on the stuffing mix, stirring until completely moist, then spread mixture on top of the chicken evenly.
The purpose of the 9 x 13-inch dish is so that stuffing mix will be taken with each helping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken with garlic butter
directions: Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Add the chicken cubes and mushrooms. Stir-fry, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Add garlic, salt and pepper to the pan. Continue to stir-fry for 3 minutes more, stirring constantly, or until the chicken cubes are cooked through.
Add butter, parsley and chicken stock to the pan. Stir-fry for 1 minute and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: summer fruit compote
directions: Combine peaches, blueberries, strawberries, melon, kiwi fruit and cherries in large bowl.
Whisk together honey, orange peel, orange juice, mint and lemon juice in small bowl.
Add dressing to fruit; toss to combine.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour in bowl.
Cut Crisco up in it.
Pour milk in.
Stir with knife, then knead.
Pat out dough and cut out biscuits.
Put in lightly greased pan.
Bake at 500° until brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain fat.
Add beans and tomatoes and blend. Bring to boil.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Prepare muffin mix according to package.
Drop by spoonfuls over meat and bean mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until top is browned in a 400° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all and bake at 475° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to milk and flavoring.
Bring to boil.
Take off heat.
Add butter.
Can be stored in Tupperware bowl in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix brown sugar and water until mixture is moist.
Bring to a rolling boil on high heat.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and blend in 1/2 jar of peanut butter until smooth.
Add remainder of peanut butter and vanilla and blend and beat until it thickens.
Spread mixture in buttered 12 x 7 x 1-inch dish.
When mixture sets solid, cut into blocks of your choice.

title: quick skillet ground beef omelet
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with the onions; add tomatoes and continue to simmer or cook on low heat.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Continue to cook on low until slightly melted.
Pour beaten eggs over mixture and simmer until done.
Serve with a salad and dinner roll.
Season as you cook to your own taste.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients; add egg and toss with fork.
Sprinkle over peaches. Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple tart
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 2 layers.
Cool baked layers and split into four thin layers.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 4-cup Pyrex measuring cup.
Add can of crushed pineapple.
Cook on High in microwave until thick and clear.
Add lemon juice and oleo.
Spread pineapple between the thin layers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter, puree half of the broccoli in the blender with 1 can of milk.
In saucepan, mix onions, all the soups and milk.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Then add cheese. This is better the day after it is made.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans well.
Press into sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes or until pecans are toasted.

title: crab meat balls
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Cut crab meat into small pieces.
Mix the two cheeses and crab meat.
Form into balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: vegetable trio
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: banana creme pie
directions: Beat whipped topping, vanilla and 1 cup of the milk for 5 minutes on high.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix; beat 2 minutes on high.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place meat in pan.
Stir together mushroom soup and onion soup mix until blended; spread over meat.
Top meat with vegetables (may also place veggies around meat) and sprinkle with water.
Cover with foil, sealing edges securely.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: chicken salad, cuban style
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl except garnish ingredients.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves; garnish with small sweet peas, canned asparagus spears (drained) and pimentos (cut into thin strips).

title: corn flake candy
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup; bring to a boil.
Take from fire; stir in vanilla, peanut butter and corn flakes.
Stir fast and well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: edible peanut butter clay
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and nonfat dry milk.
Let children shape the mixture into balls, snakes, people, etc...You can provide peanuts, raisins, chocolate chips, coconut or something else for them to decorate their creations.
They may nibble as they work.
A cookie sheet provides a good work surface.

title: sugar-free coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix pie filling, milk and 1/2 to 3/4 cup grated fresh coconut.
Bring to a boil. Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill.
Mix topping mix according to package directions.
Put desired amount of topping on chilled pie. In ungreased skillet, toast 2 tablespoons grated fresh coconut until golden.
Sprinkle on top of whipped topping.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender at one time and blend until mixed together.
Pour into buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When done, crust will be on the bottom, custard in the middle and coconut on the top, right where it belongs.

title: brownies
directions: For brownies, mix flour, sugar, and salt. In saucepan put margarine, water, and cocoa. Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture and stir. Beat egg. Add buttermilk and baking soda. Add to flour mixture. Add vanilla. Bake in 12 x 9-inch shallow pan that is well greased and floured. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. While cake is hot, frost it with icing. When slightly cool cut into squares.

title: swamp cabbage
directions: Clean and cut swamp cabbages.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cut bacon in small pieces and stir-fry.
When cabbage begins to become tender, add bacon and stir.
Continue to cook until tender.
Remove from heat and add milk.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan with waxed paper. Mix ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Invert onto towel or pillowcase sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Cool about 10 minutes (or while making filling).
Remove paper.
Cover with filling; roll.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to
a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes; remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Slowly pour over corn, mixing well.
Pour into 2 large shallow baking pans or roasting pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and break apart.
When cool, store in tightly covered container.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend softened butter or margarine with sugar.
Beat eggs, one at a time, with first mixture.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix vanilla last.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: play-clay
directions: Will also need shaping tools (like a knife), toothpicks, cookie cutter, rolling pin, cake rack, paints and brush.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush 1 cup fresh strawberries and cook with water about 2 minutes; sieve.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; stir into berry juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add a few drops red food coloring.

title: almost peanut butter cups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and spread in a lightly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour melted chocolate over this mixture. Allow to cool.
Cut in squares.

title: bavarian beans
directions: Mix. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy microwave peanut brittle
