directions: Mix sugar and syrup well in 1 1/2-quart casserole or bowl and nuke 4 minutes on High.
Add peanuts; stir and nuke 2:45 to 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; blend well and nuke 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be light brown and syrup hot.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy and quickly pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour and break into pieces. Makes about 1 pound.
Work fast after adding soda because it hardens fast.
Delicious.

title: spiced highbush cranberry sauce or catsup
directions: Cook the cranberries in the water until soft, then put through a food mill or a sieve.
Add the onions, vinegar, sugar, spices, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Boil until the mixture thickens and reaches the proper consistency.
Pour into hot jars and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in pan. Add scallions and garlic and cook briefly. Add noodles and cook over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Bring broth to full boil in separate pan and add to the rice mixture. Cover tightly and simmer for 35 minutes. Do not stir or remove lid. Remove from heat. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir well and chill.

title: rice surprise
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, layer the ingredients in the order given.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring after 20 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar together, then add eggs.
Mix vanilla wafers and coconut together, then add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in a few drops of red food color and cool.

title: danny's hamburger soup with peas
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
If you want to keep it low-fat wash the meat in a colander with hot water.
Peel and cut into small pieces the potatoes.
Put the meat, potatoes, salt, pepper, garlic, tomatoes and sauce into large soup pan.
Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are almost done.
Drain and add all ingredients.
Continue cooking until potatoes are well done.
Don't add peas unless you like them.
Danny doesn't.

title: sunday chicken enchiladas
directions: Begin at 12:05 or 12:15, time variable with visitation.
Blend with other traffic on 23rd Street and proceed 4 1/2 miles west. Proceed south for 2 more miles.
Mix with other cars for best parking spot.
Beat pavement for 2 to 3 minutes until able to pour through door.
Simmer while waiting in line for 15 minutes.
Stuff with salsa and chips for another 10 minutes until full.
Eat enchiladas while still hot and top off with Rolaids and 45 minute nap.
Thank Carol for another delicious meal.

title: mock mimosa
directions: Combine the orange juice and diet soda.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 375° in large casserole dish.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter, stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake for 1 hour in 250° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: lime jello salad for dieters
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well and chill.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: homemade pie crust
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a mixer. Mix until smooth. Half mixture. Put flour on wax paper. Lay half of flour mixture on wax paper. Sprinkle enough flour on top of flour mixture to keep it from sticking to wax paper that you put on top to roll out crust. Roll out mixture as thin as you can. Lift top wax paper up carefully so bottom piece of wax paper comes off of crust. Gently lay crust and wax paper onto an 8 or 9-inch pie plate. Gently remove wax paper off around plate, but leave enough to turn under on edge to make a smooth edging. Crink edge if you like. Poke holes in bottom and sides of crust. Bake at 350° for around 15 to 20 minutes. Take out and pour in favorite filling.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and onion.
Drain off grease and add sausage, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles until tender; drain.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Arrange lasagna in baking dish in layers, alternating with layers of meat sauce, cottage cheese, then another layer of noodles, sauce and cottage cheese until you have 4 layers.
Then top off with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together thoroughly, then add remaining ingredients.
Combine and mix well; pour in 9 x 13 lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350°.
Bake until toothpick comes from center clean (about 45 to 50 minutes).

title: cheese herb bread
directions: Add to dry roll mix the basil and oregano.
Mix according to directions on box.
Let rise.
Roll out dough in a rectangle. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and grated sharp cheese.
Roll jelly roll style and form a circle, joining the two ends.
Cut slits in top and let rise.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy fruit frost
directions: Stir soft cream cheese into whipped topping.
Gradually add cherry pie filling.
Fold in other fruit.
Pour into a 2-cup mold. Freeze overnight until firm.
Let stand out 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine 1/2 package of cream cheese and 1 jar shrimp cocktail. Whip together in blender.
Remove from blender and repeat with other half.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except the pineapple.
Beat until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
While cake is hot, pour pineapple over it.
Allow to soak through.
Let cake cool before frosting.

title: cerra chili
directions: Combine the ground beef, onions and water in a saucepan. Simmer the ingredients until the beef browns.
Add the tomatoes and their juice along with the vinegar, Worcestershire, chili powder, cumin, allspice, salt, cayenne, cinnamon, garlic powder and bay leaves.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.

title: apple noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain in colander. Rinse with cold water.
Meanwhile, combine walnuts, apples, raisins and spices.
Beat egg yolks with butter, sugar and salt. Fold egg yolk mixture into hot noodles.
Fold in fruits and spices.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in.
Bake in well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and add cream cheese, stirring until melted.
Add gelatin and stir until thickened.
Add other ingredients and seasonings to taste.
Pour into 1-quart greased fish-shaped mold. Chill overnight.
Serve on red leaf lettuce with assorted crackers.

title: beefy spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in paste.
Serve with French bread.

title: fantastic peanut butter crunch
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine.
Add peanut butter.
As soon as melted, take off of heat.
Add sugar.
Stir in Rice Krispies and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bars.
Ice top of candy while warm.
Set aside to harden.
Do not refrigerate.
Takes about 3 hours to harden enough to slice. Makes 30 to 40 servings.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs, vanilla and flour good. Bake at 325°.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in boiling water, stirring until both are dissolved; cool.
Beat in cream cheese. Refrigerate until almost congealed.
Remove from refrigerator and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple, whipped cream and nuts. Congeal in long shallow pan, cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: mango brown betty
directions: Melt the butter and add bread crumbs.
Place a layer of the buttered bread crumbs in a oiled baking dish.
Add a layer of mango.
Sprinkle the fruit with sugar and cinnamon and add another layer of crumbs.
Add another layer of mango.
Place more crumbs on top.
Bake in moderate oven for about 1 hour or until mangoes are soft.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Run hot water over broccoli and place in dish.
Dice green onion and sprinkle over broccoli.
Drain chestnuts.
Pour over top.
Mix cheese, soup and sour cream together.
Pour over top of broccoli.
Pour bread crumbs over top. Cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken wings with honey and orange sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tips off chicken wings (save tips for sauce).
Halve remaining chicken wings at joint.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, blend remaining ingredients.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Bake uncovered, basting occasionally, 40 minutes or until chicken is done and sauce is thickened.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar, then egg yolks; beat to cream consistency.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time.
When well mixed, add nuts.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot dogs
directions: Start grill.
Cook on grill for minute.
Put in a roll with ketchup and other stuff.
Eat it all gone.

title: fried artichoke hearts
directions: Drain and cut hearts in quarters.
Pat dry.
Soak in egg wash. Cover with bread crumbs.
Fry in oil until they float.
Drain. Season to taste and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over them.
Good hot or cold!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk, then add whipped topping.
Mix all together well; pour into graham cracker shell.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Chill until firm before cutting.

title: red hot salad
directions: Combine pineapple and red hots. Let set overnight at room temperature. Stir together whipped topping and marshmallows. Stir into pineapple and red hots; refrigerate.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Put sliced strawberries in shell.
Boil cornstarch, NutraSweet, Jell-O and water until thick.
Pour boiled mixture over strawberries.
Chill and top with lite Cool Whip or box of diet D-Zerta topping.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cut dates in chunks.
Cut cherries in quarters.
Cut pineapple in thin slices and add to the nuts.
Mix well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Cream butter, add sugar gradually and eggs. Beat thoroughly.
Combine the sifted flour mixture with the butter, sugar and egg mixture. Mix well.
Add the fruit and nuts. Mix well (heat oven).
Drop batter from teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at
350° temperature.
Don't overbake.
Cookies are much nicer and chewy.

title: party punch
directions: Add concentrate to 2 quarts soda and 1 quart cranberry juice. Mix in remaining soda.
Scoop sherbet on top 15 minutes before serving.

title: heart of palms
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Drain and chop hearts of palm. Set aside 1 Tbsp. parmesan.
Combine all other ingredients, mix well.
Spread into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove and mix again.
Serve as a dip or spread on crackers, bread or pita bread.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pile into baked pie shell. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from side of filling comes out clean.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Layer sliced eggplant in a colander and sprinkle with salt. Add another layer and sprinkle with salt and so on until all of the eggplant slices are in the colander.
This process will allow the eggplant to extract its water.
Leave on a counter for an hour and allow to drain.

title: amaretto-chocolate sauce
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir until well blended.
Add cream, bourbon and vanilla.
Bring mixture just to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Reheat to serve over slices of pound cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: *bulgur with cottage cheese and feta cheese(turcanoinia)
directions: Warm milk.
Add butter and a dash of salt.
Bring to a boil and add bulgur, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes, while boiling.
Remove from heat.
Cover and set aside for at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package instructions.
Drain and mix well with all other ingredients.
Bake uncovered in casserole dish for 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: half baked beans
directions: Mix and bake in a covered dish 1 hour at 350°.
Stir when done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In skillet, combine chicken, vegetables and broth; simmer 10 minutes.
Thicken broth with flour; season with salt and pepper. In pie plate, place 1 pie shell and pour in meat-vegetable mixture.
Top with the other pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Place 1/2 of potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and top with cheese slices.
Add remaining potatoes.
Place chops on potatoes.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper. Saute onion and celery in skillet drippings until tender.
Add soup and milk to skillet; heat and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: 1. Food process (or finely chop) Artichokes then add rest of ingredients.
2. pour into greased 8 X 8 baking dish.
3. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
4. Serve with sliced French bread.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes and onion.
Mix with the salt and pepper.
Turn into 1-quart casserole. Add butter and water to the top. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole with parmesan(microwave recipe)
directions: Place potatoes and water in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook on High 10 to 12 minutes or until steaming. Drain. Add milk, salt, chives and butter.
Stir carefully, then stir in Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium 8 to 9 minutes or until tender.

title: bill's no bake fruitcake
directions: In a large bowl, crush graham crackers fine.
Add fruit, raisins, chopped nuts and sliced cherries (keep a few nuts and halved cherries for decoration).
Heat milk and add marshmallows; stir frequently.
Heat until the marshmallows are melted and the mixture is smooth.
Add to "cake" mixture and blend thoroughly. Line a fairly large (or 2 small) cookie tin with foil.
Place a small glass in the center of the tin and pack mixture around the glass firmly.
When finished, carefully remove glass.
Cover tin and refrigerate for two weeks before serving.
Will keep up to four months.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add meat and brown. Drain excess fat. Add other ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Even better if served following day.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans. Form a ball. Roll in pecans. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry nut loaf
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla; beat.
Add strawberries. Combine flour, soda, powder and salt, then add gradually to strawberry mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces.
Prepare instant pudding and mix with Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.
Mix sliced strawberries with glaze and pour over pudding.

title: heather's maple sweet potatoes
directions: Combine syrup and butter in a saucepan; bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Add sweet potatoes.
Simmer until hot, basting occasionally with glaze.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy rocky road bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Add marshmallows and peanuts.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla in bowl, beat thoroughly.
Mix flour, salt and soda and oats in mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.

title: parmesan treats
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and chill.
Spread on rye bread and put under broiler until lightly browned.

title: pecan krispies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Add pecans.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. For decoration, put 1 pecan half on top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1 cup of the Chinese noodles.
Pour into a casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining cup of noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maryland crab dip
directions: Mix and chill before serving, on or with crackers.

title: lemon spice tea
directions: In a microwave mug, combine water, honey, lemon slice and cinnamon. Micro-cook mixture, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 minutes or just until steaming hot. Add tea bag. Cover and steep for 4 minutes. Remove tea bag, lemon slice and cinnamon. Garnish with an additional lemon slice if desired.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter, milk and vanilla.

title: company best pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Repeat this for 3 more days.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Do not roll; drop on greased pan from spoon 3 to 4 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: psalms 45
directions: Grace to be justified freely.
Favor to be sweet.
Mercy for everlasting, faith to be loyalty and peace to be calm and still. Compassion of one another.
Jesus moved with compassion.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix all but bread in a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish; add bread and stir.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water, about 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Mix all.
Pour into freezer container or electric ice cream maker.

title: chicken waikiki
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in flour and fry in oil for a few minutes until slightly browned.
Put in casserole pan.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place onion, mustard, Accent, salt and vinegar in mixer; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and stir in gradually.
Mix well and place in a 1-quart container.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican dip(seven layer dip)
directions: Mix taco seasoning with refried beans. Layer and eat with large, round, plain Tostitos.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel raw pears and cut into quarters.
To each pound of pears, add 1
pound
sugar.
Cook over medium heat until syrup is thick and
pears	are tender.
Cover and seal in sterilized jars.

title: pumpkin bread(easy)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 3 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in nuts and raisins (optional).
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaves from pans; remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap tightly.

title: sangria
directions: Pour wine into a 4-quart non-metallic pitcher.
Add lemon juice and all of the cut fruit.
Stir in the sugar and brandy with a wooden spoon.
Add cinnamon and stir again.
Add ice cubes and stir once more.
The mixture should be allowed to stand for at least 30 minutes before serving, although it can be left overnight.
Serve chilled with some of the fruit in each glass ... spoons are optional!

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients except wine and chili sauce.
Form into loaf.
Place in roaster with 3/4 c. water.
Combine wine and chili sauce.
Pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 2 hours or to desired doneness.

title: baked swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into serving size pieces.
Heat oil in skillet; brown steak.
Season with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Cover with onions.
In skillet, heat tomatoes; add Worcestershire sauce and season to taste.
Pour over steak; cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: kitchen floor pickles
directions: Fill a gallon jar with washed pickles.
Add pickling salt, alum, pickling spices and vinegar.
Fill remainder of jar with water.
Place lid on jar and let set for a month.
Drain and wash pickles.
Rinse in clear water.
Cut in thin slices.
Place in jar and add sugar; shake jar until pickles are covered with juice. Process, if desired.
Or can be kept in refrigerator.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate over low heat.
Cool a few minutes. Then add vanilla and pecans.
Sift flour and sugar; add eggs and stir lightly until flour is absorbed.
Stir in chocolate mixture. Do not use mixer.
Fill paper muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers in half and boil until tender but not too soft.
Cook the ground meat and drain.
Fry the shrimp and drain also.
Mix the ground meat, shrimp and the stuffed crabs in a big bowl with the rice and one can of tomato sauce.
Mix well and put into peppers and cook for 1 hour.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add oysters.
Cook 3 minutes over moderate heat, until edges of oysters curl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let heat almost to boiling point.
Serve at once. Sprinkle paprika on each serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, plain flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Place cherries on paper towels to absorb juice. In a bowl mix sugar, butter, syrup and salt. Knead until smooth, refrigerate 1 hour. Roll into 1/2 inch balls, flatten and wrap around a cherry. Place on waxed paper and refrigerate 1 hour. Melt together chocolate chips and 4 Tbsp. butter. Stir until smooth. Dip cherry centers in chocolate, set back on wax paper and refrigerate until hardened. Place chocolates in a covered container and refrigerate for 1-2 weeks to set up.

title: panas or scrapple(german breakfast food)
directions: Cover meat with water and add spices.
Cook until meat is tender.
Cool.
Coarsely grind meat.
Return to broth.
Mix corn meal with flour and sugar.
Start adding the dry ingredients. Stir, stir, stir until it thickens.
Cook over low heat until panas pulls away from spoon or pan.
Add more spices to suit taste or leave as is.
Pour into bread pans.
Cool, then store in refrigerator or freezer.
Place waxed paper between slices.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until nearly tender. Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and let set for 12 hours. Will keep 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: strawberry marbled cheesecake
directions: In blender container, combine strawberries and cornstarch; blend until smooth.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Reserve 1/3 cup of sauce; cool.
Chill remaining sauce.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix and roll
into small balls.
Roll balls in coconut, powdered sugar or nuts.

title: orange cookies
directions: Beat all this together besides flour.
Then sift flour and baking powder and stir in gradually.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
(This is a soft cookie.)

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Cook chicken in water. Take chicken out when cooked and cut up into pieces. Add to broth the onion, carrots, mushrooms, bouillon cubes and 1 box Uncle Ben's original recipe wild rice. Pour all ingredients into stock. Boil 1 cup long grain white rice until rice is tender.

Add cream of celery soup and cream of chicken with herbs. Fill both cans with water and add to thin out the soup to achieve desired thickness. Heat up again. Add salt and pepper or favorite seasonings if you want spicier soup.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In bowl, pour oleo over crushed pretzels.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar; add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour over pretzels; cool.
Mix hot water and Jell-O; stir well.
Put frozen strawberries in hot Jell-O mixture.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: baked herbed potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, basil and pepper.
Halve potatoes lengthwise. Brush cut surface with lemon mixture, then dip into cheese mixture.
Place coated side down in a spoke pattern on a glass pie plate.
Microwave on High 14 to 16 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn once.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding per box directions.
Add Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of graham cracker squares.
Cover crackers with half the pudding mixture.
Repeat the layer.
Top these with one more layer of graham crackers.
Cover the top layer (graham crackers) with your choice of frosting.
Cover with clear wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple pizza
directions: Mix the cinnamon and sugar together; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place biscuits on baking sheet.
Put an apple slice on each biscuit; dot with butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on top of biscuit; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until biscuits are brown and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chess cake
directions: Sift together the flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa and water;
pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk,
eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on bottom of cooled pie crust. Place strawberries point up in cream cheese tightly together so that the pie shell is full.
Spread Marie's pie glaze over strawberries to fill in spaces.
Refrigerate before serving and top with Cool Whip.

title: banana bread
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: smoked beef dip
directions: Mix everything together except nuts.
Add nuts to the top and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: seven bean soup
directions: Combine all beans.
Yields nine 2-cup packages.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Mix beef, 1 egg, onion, rice, parsley, mint, oil and 1/4 cup water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Soak fresh leaves in warm water 5 minutes.
If canned leaves are used, rinse in warm water.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer cheese on bottom of casserole dish, then the mayo, taco mix, then top with layer of shredded cheese, shredded lettuce, chopped onions, chopped green peppers and chopped tomatoes.
Eat with Dorito chips.
Use a square cake pan.

title: egg pie
directions: Blend all 5 ingredients together with a blender or a mixer. Pour in 9 or 8-inch pie crust.
This mixture will make 2 pies.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in refrigerator in a covered container.
Do not put barbecue sauce on meat until it is almost cooked.
Baste meat with sauce and turn 4 or 5 times.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl; blend well.
Bring to rapid boil in saucepan the margarine, shortening, water and cocoa and pour over flour-sugar mixture and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and add all at once to batter, mixing well.
Pour into greased, lightly floured sheet pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: carolyn's casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown beef and pour off excess fat. Stir in sauce.
Combine meat mixture with noodles.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: basic white bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved dry yeast in a large bowl.
Combine water, milk and margarine in a saucepan. Heat over low heat until warm.
Add egg to liquid mixture.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Add rest of flour (3 1/2 to 4 1/2 cups), make a soft, smooth dough by kneading.
Put in a greased bowl (turn to have greased side on top).
Cover; let rise until doubled (1 hour).

title: baked sole with mushrooms
directions: Arrange fish in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with wine. Blend cream, mushrooms, cornstarch and salt.
Pour mix over fish. Bake at 325° (basting often) 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: eggless egg salad
directions: Mix well.
Serve open-faced on bread.
Garnish with alfalfa sprouts.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: In skillet in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and broccoli is tender, stirring often.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven in 2 tablespoons hot shortening.
Add 2 cups hot water, spices and seasonings.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Beat baking mix, margarine, garlic salt and eggs until well blended.
Stir in zucchini, green onions and Parmesan cheese. Grease heated pan.
Use 1/4 cup of mixture for each patty.
Spread slightly.
Cook until dry around the edges.
Turn and cook until golden.
Makes 12 pancakes.
Serve as side dish.

title: beer batter
directions: In bowl with fork, mix first 3 ingredients.
In another bowl, beat together beer, egg and 2 tablespoons of oil; stir liquid into flour mixture.
Deep fry chicken until done.
Works great on onion rings, too.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish, 9 x 11-inches.
Make batter of sugar,
flour,
milk
and baking powder.
Pour over melted butter. Do not stir.
Pour peaches over batter.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: oven crisp chicken
directions: Combine soup mix, bread crumbs, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces, a few at a time, in the mixture to coat well.
Place, not touching, in a single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and richly browned.

title: fruity ham glaze
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
About 30 minutes before ham is done, remove from oven.
Score surface; spoon glaze over entire ham.
Return to oven, basting occasionally during last 30 minutes of baking.

title: granola bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and oats.
Press half the dough firmly into bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Spread apple butter over top. Sprinkle with remaining dough; press lightly.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes. Cut into bars.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: venison stew
directions: Trim fat from venison and brown in a skillet with oil.
In a large kettle, boil 6 cups of water.
Add venison, bay leaf, carrots, celery, potatoes and onions.
Boil for 20 minutes, then reduce heat.
Add curry powder, lemon juice and ground garlic. Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Add sliced green peppers.
Add flour to thicken.
Serves 4.
Preparation Time:
4 hours.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Use flat oblong casserole dish. Slice bread into strips (remove crusts, if you desire).
Melt butter and margarine. Arrange strips of bread in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter and margarine over bread, saturating it.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased (hot) skillet. Bake at 425 until brown.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough thin and cut with favorite cookie cutter.
Place on oiled cookie sheet; sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mom robertson's tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add tuna.
Meanwhile, heat milk and as much chopped onion as desired over low heat.
Add cream of celery soup and chunks of Velveeta.
Heat until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over tuna and macaroni.
Top with slices of Velveeta.
Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 1 large casserole.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into wedges.
Cook until tender.
Peel and chop onion and red pepper.
In skillet saute 1 tablespoon butter and ground meat.
Add pepper, onion and garlic.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add vinegar, parsley and bay leaf.
Cook for a few minutes.
Transfer mixture to a lightly greased plate. Drain potatoes.
Mash.
Add remaining butter, spices and half and half.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread mashed potatoes over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until pie is hot and potatoes are lightly browned.
Good served with green salad.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Saute rice in oil, over low heat, until golden brown (5 to 10 minutes).
Spread rice in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Layer onion, green pepper, zucchini and tomatoes over rice.
Add salt and garlic to broth, then pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed and vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well before using.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil together for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 cups oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper and cool completely.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat the shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, soda and salt, then stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fluffy salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add oranges and pineapple. Mix.
Then stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Good with other flavors of jello and different fruits.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix following ingredients in a 6 to 8-quart container:
Hershey bars (broken into pieces), Hershey's Kisses, marshmallow cream and margarine.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until flavors are well blended.

title: jello cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple with juice.
Chill until partially set.
Layer half in dish, cover with sour cream.
Top with rest of Jell-O mixture.
Chill
until firm.

title: moussaka
directions: Brown onion and cloves.
Add tomatoes (chopped), basil, salt, cinnamon and lemon.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Slice eggplant and brown on cookie sheet in oven; brush with oil.
Layer 1/2 eggplant in greased pie pan.
Pour 1/2 sauce over eggplant.
Repeat.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: To soften sugar:
To keep brown sugar soft and fresh, remove it from the box and place it in a plastic bag with holes; then seal the top tightly with a rubber band or wire tie.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix veggies, sour cream, soup, onion and water chestnuts together. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Crush crackers and spread evenly over vegetable mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine or butter over crumbs.
Bake uncovered for approximately 1 hour at 375°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: three cheese delight casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off liquid.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 1 minute.
Stir in cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and noodles.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 350° for 30 minutes.

title: simple beef dinner(simple and delicious!)
directions: Cut stew meat in smaller pieces.
Add onion, cut in chunks. Brown.
Add about 1 cup water; simmer until partially tender.
Add carrots; cut in pieces.
(Also add other raw vegetables, if desired.)
Cook until meat and vegetables are tender.
Add golden cream of mushroom soup for gravy mixture.
Serve over cooked noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: hungarian chicken paprikas
directions: Saute onion in Crisco until lightly brown.
Add chicken, paprika and enough water to almost cover.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook slowly until chicken is tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Mix flour and water along with sour cream; blend well.
Remove chicken, add cream mixture to drippings. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over dumplings or noodles.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Beat all together to thicken with electric beater.
Pour into pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: brisket roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll brisket in mixture and wrap in foil loosely.
Cook for 6 hours at 300°.
Cooking the brisket a long time at a low heat will make it very tender.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine the 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt; stir in water. Bring to boiling over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly, until thick, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to remaining mixture in pan. Bring to boil and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add lemon peel and butter; slowly stir in 1/3 cup

lemon juice. Cool to lukewarm. Pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites with 1 teaspoon lemon juice until soft peaks form. Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar; beat until stiff. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Blend together cocoa, sugar, flour, vanilla, and salt. Add milk to mixture; mix all ingredients well and cook.

title: eggnog pudding
directions: Prepare instant vanilla pudding as directed.
Add brandy flavoring.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Dash with nutmeg.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix well and pour on top of first layer. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Allow to cool before cutting.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk together.
Boil 2 minutes. Take off stove.
Add peanut butter and oats and drop by spoonful (tablespoon) onto aluminum foil.
Add 1/2 cup nuts or coconut, if desired.

title: low-fat turkey casserole
directions: Cook turkey meat and chopped onions (don't brown).
Drain any grease.
Add mushroom soup, chicken noodle soup, milk and uncooked rice.
Put in a buttered casserole dish.
The last 1/2 hour, top with fat-free grated cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Add vanilla, milk and nutmeg; mix.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican addiction
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas. Spread mixture on tortillas. Roll tortillas tightly and chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Cut ends off each tortilla roll. Slice tortilla rolls 1/4 to 3/4 inch slices. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika and buns.
Split 6 or 7 buns, butter each side.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place tuna on buns.
Wrap each individually in foil.
Place on a cookie sheet. Heat in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overheat.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In skillet in 1 tablespoon of olive oil, cook zucchini, peppers and onion until tender and golden.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, black pepper and seasonings; heat to boiling.
Reduce to low and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
